    #' @description This method extracts profiles of values from the array of

                    		
                  

                  

                    756
                    
                    
                      
    #'   the variable, with the location along each axis to extract expressed in

                    		
                  

                  

                    757
                    
                    
                      
    #'   coordinate values of each axis.

                    		
                  

                  

                    758
                    
                    
                      
    #'

                    		
                  

                  

                    759
                    
                    
                      
    #' @details The coordinates along each axis to be sampled are expressed in

                    		
                  

                  

                    760
                    
                    
                      
    #'   values of the domain of the axis. Any axes which are not passed as

                    		
                  

                  

                    761
                    
                    
                      
    #'   arguments are extracted in whole to the result. If bounds are set on

                    		
                  

                  

                    762
                    
                    
                      
    #'   the axis, the coordinate whose bounds envelop the requested coordinate

                    		
                  

                  

                    763
                    
                    
                      
    #'   is selected. Otherwise, the coordinate along the axis closest to the

                    		
                  

                  

                    764
                    
                    
                      
    #'   supplied value will be used. If the value for a specified axis falls

                    		
                  

                  

                    765
                    
                    
                      
    #'   outside the valid range of that axis, `NULL` is returned.

                    		
                  

                  

                    766
                    
                    
                      
    #'

                    		
                  

                  

                    767
                    
                    
                      
    #'   A typical case is to extract the temporal profile as a 1D array for a

                    		
                  

                  

                    768
                    
                    
                      
    #'   given location. In this case, use arguments for the latitude and

                    		
                  

                  

                    769
                    
                    
                      
    #'   longitude on an X-Y-T data variable: `profile(lat = -24, lon = 3)`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    770
                    
                    
                      
    #'   Other profiling options are also possible, such as a 2D zonal

                    		
                  

                  

                    771
                    
                    
                      
    #'   atmospheric profile at a given longitude for an X-Y-Z data variable:

                    		
                  

                  

                    772
                    
                    
                      
    #'   `profile(lon = 34)`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    773
                    
                    
                      
    #'

                    		
                  

                  

                    774
                    
                    
                      
    #'   Multiple profiles can be extracted in one call by supplying vectors for

                    		
                  

                  

                    775
                    
                    
                      
    #'   the indicated axes: `profile(lat = c(-24, -23, -2), lon = c(5, 5, 6))`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    776
                    
                    
                      
    #'   The vectors need not have the same length, unless `.as_table = TRUE`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    777
                    
                    
                      
    #'   With unequal length vectors the result will be a `list` of `CFVariable`

                    		
                  

                  

                    778
                    
                    
                      
    #'   instances with different dimensionality and/or different axes.

                    		
                  

                  

                    779
                    
                    
                      
    #'

                    		
                  

                  

                    780
                    
                    
                      
    #'   ## Auxiliary coordinate variables

                    		
                  

                  

                    781
                    
                    
                      
    #'

                    		
                  

                  

                    782
                    
                    
                      
    #'   A special case exists for variables where the horizontal dimensions (X

                    		
                  

                  

                    783
                    
                    
                      
    #'   and Y) are not in longitude and latitude coordinates but in some other

                    		
                  

                  

                    784
                    
                    
                      
    #'   coordinate system. In this case the netCDF resource may have so-called

                    		
                  

                  

                    785
                    
                    
                      
    #'   *auxiliary coordinate variables*. If the variable has such *auxiliary coordinate

                    		
                  

                  

                    786
                    
                    
                      
    #'   variables* then you can specify their names (instead of specifying the

                    		
                  

                  

                    787
                    
                    
                      
    #'   names of the primary planar axes).

                    		
                  

                  

                    788
                    
                    
                      
    #' @param ... One or more arguments of the form `axis = location`. The

                    		
                  

                  

                    789
                    
                    
                      
    #'   "axis" part should be the name of an axis or its orientation `X`, `Y`,

                    		
                  

                  

                    790
                    
                    
                      
    #'   `Z` or `T`. The "location" part is a vector of values representing

                    		
                  

                  

                    791
                    
                    
                      
    #'   coordinates along the axis where to profile. A profile will be

                    		
                  

                  

                    792
                    
                    
                      
    #'   generated for each of the elements of the "location" vectors in all

                    		
                  

                  

                    793
                    
                    
                      
    #'   arguments.

                    		
                  

                  

                    794
                    
                    
                      
    #' @param .names A character vector with names for the results. The names

                    		
                  

                  

                    795
                    
                    
                      
    #'   will be used for the resulting `CFVariable` instances, or as values for

                    		
                  

                  

                    796
                    
                    
                      
    #'   the "location" column of the `data.table` if argument `.as_table` is

                    		
                  

                  

                    797
                    
                    
                      
    #'   `TRUE`. If the vector is shorter than the longest vector of locations

    profile = function(..., .names = NULL, .as_table = FALSE) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    811
                    4x

                    4x

                    813
                    !

                    840
                    4x

                    841
                    4x

                    8x

                    8x

                    8x

    #' @description Append the data from another `CFVariable` instance to the

                    		
                  

                  

                    927

    append = function(from, along) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    938

                    939
                    3x

                    3x

    #' @description Convert the data to a `terra::SpatRaster` (3D) or a

    #' @return A `terra::SpatRaster` or `terra::SpatRasterDataset` instance.

    terra = function() {

                    		
                  

                  

                    971
                    1x
                    
                      
      if (!requireNamespace("terra", quietly = TRUE))

                    !

    },

                    1020
                    
                    
                      
    #' @description Retrieve the data variable in the object in the form of a

                    1027
                    
                    
                      
    #' @param var_as_column Logical to flag if the name of the variable should

                    		
                  

                  

                    1028

                    1029

                    1030

    #' @return A `data.table` with all data points in individual rows. All axes

                    1034

    data.table = function(var_as_column = FALSE) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    1036
                    1x
                    
                      
      if (!requireNamespace("data.table", quietly = TRUE))

                    		
                  

                  

                    1037
                    !

                    1038
                    1x

#' Extract data for a variable

                    		
                  

                  

                    1197
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    1198
                    
                    
                      
#' Extract data from a `CFVariable` instance, optionally sub-setting the

                    		
                  

                  

                    1199
                    
                    
                      
#' axes to load only data of interest.

                    		
                  

                  

                    1200
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    1201
                    
                    
                      
#' If all the data of the variable in `x` is to be extracted, simply use `[]`

                    		
                  

                  

                    1202
                    
                    
                      
#' (unlike with regular arrays, this is required, otherwise the details of the

                    		
                  

                  

                    1203
                    
                    
                      
#' variable are printed on the console).

                    		
                  

                  

                    1204
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    1205
                    
                    
                      
#' The indices into the axes to be subset can be specified in a variety of

                    		
                  

                  

                    1206
                    
                    
                      
#' ways; in practice it should (resolve to) be a vector of integers. A range

                    		
                  

                  

                    1207
                    
                    
                      
#' (e.g. `100:200`), an explicit vector (`c(23, 46, 3, 45, 17`), a sequence

                    		
                  

                  

                    1208
                    
                    
                      
#' (`seq(from = 78, to = 100, by = 2`), all work. Note, however, that only a

                    		
                  

                  

                    1209
                    
                    
                      
#' single range is generated from the vector so these examples resolve to

                    		
                  

                  

                    1210
                    
                    
                      
#' `100:200`, `3:46`, and `78:100`, respectively. It is also possible to use a

                    		
                  

                  

                    1211
                    
                    
                      
#' custom function as an argument.

                    		
                  

                  

                    1212
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    1213
                    
                    
                      
#' This method works with "bare" indices into the axes of the array. If

                    		
                  

                  

                    1214
                    
                    
                      
#' you want to use domain values of the axes (e.g. longitude values or

                    		
                  

                  

                    1215
                    
                    
                      
#' timestamps) to extract part of the variable array, use the

                    		
                  

                  

                    1216
                    
                    
                      
#' `CFVariable$subset()` method.

                    		
                  

                  

                    1217
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    1218
                    
                    
                      
#' Scalar axes should not be included in the indexing as they do not represent a

                    		
                  

                  

                    1219
                    
                    
                      
#' dimension into the data array.

                    		
                  

                  

                    1220
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    1221
                    
                    
                      
#' @param x An `CFVariable` instance to extract the data of.

                    		
                  

                  

                    1222
                    
                    
                      
#' @param i,j,... Expressions, one for each axis of `x`, that select a

                    		
                  

                  

                    1223
                    
                    
                      
#'   number of elements along each axis. If any expressions are missing,

                    		
                  

                  

                    1224
                    
                    
                      
#'   the entire axis is extracted. The values for the arguments may be an

                    		
                  

                  

                    1225
                    
                    
                      
#'   integer vector or a function that returns an integer vector. The range of

                    		
                  

                  

                    1226
                    
                    
                      
#'   the values in the vector will be used. See examples, below.

                    		
                  

                  

                    1227
                    
                    
                      
#' @param drop Logical, ignored. Axes are never dropped. Any degenerate

                    		
                  

                  

                    1228
                    
                    
                      
#'   dimensions of the array are returned as such, with dimnames and appropriate

                    		
                  

                  

                    1229
                    
                    
                      
#'   attributes set.

                    		
                  

                  

                    1230
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    1231
                    
                    
                      
#' @return An array with dimnames and other attributes set.

                    		
                  

                  

                    1232
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    1233
                    
                    
                      
#' @aliases bracket_select

                    		
                  

                  

                    1234
                    
                    
                      
#' @docType methods

                    		
                  

                  

                    1235
                    
                    
                      
#' @examples

                    		
                  

                  

                    1236
                    
                    
                      
#' fn <- system.file("extdata",

                    		
                  

                  

                    1237

# This function is a bare-bones implementation of `apply(X, MARGIN, tapply, INDEX, FUN, ...)`,

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
# i.e. apply a factor over a dimension of an array. There are several restrictions

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
# compared to the base::apply/tapply pair (but note that function arguments are

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
# named differently): (1) X must be a vector, matrix or array (not a data.frame);

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
# (2) MARGIN must have all dimensions except the one to operate on; (3) INDEX is

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
# therefore a single factor; (4) MARGIN must be numeric (not dimnames); (5) FUN

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
# must be a function (not a formula); and (6) FUN must return a vector of numeric

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
# values, with each call generating the same number of values. In the interest of

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
# speed, these restrictions are not tested. Furthermore, no dimnames

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
# are set and the result is always simplified to a vector, matrix or array.

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
# On the up side, this function always returns a list, with as many elements as

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      
# FUN returns values. If oper > 1L, the dimensions of the result are rearranged

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    
                    
                      
# such that the dimension that is operated on comes first with the others

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      
# following. This is identical to the tapply output.

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    
                    
                      
#

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    
                    
                      
# The basic version without a factor is about 10% faster than the base::apply()

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    
                    
                      
# function. When used with a factor, this code is twice as fast as apply/tapply.

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    
                    
                      
#

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    
                    
                      
# Arguments:

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    
                    
                      
# X    - Vector, matrix or array

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    
                    
                      
# oper - The ordinal number of the axis to operate on

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    
                    
                      
# fac  - The factor over whose levels to apply FUN, or NULL if no levels

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    
                    
                      
# FUN  - The function to call with the data

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    
                    
                      
# ...  - Additional arguments passed on to FUN

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    
                    
                      
.process.data <- function (X, oper, fac = NULL, FUN, ...) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    
                    
                      
  # FUN must return a vector of atomic types. A list is explicitly not going to

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    
                    
                      
  # work. Every call over the fac levels must return the same number of values.

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    5x
                    
                      
  FUN <- match.fun(FUN)

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    
                    
                      
  # Number of distinct groups in the data, if fac is supplied

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    5x
                    
                      
  nl <- if (is.factor(fac)) nlevels(fac) else 1L

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    5x
                    
                      
  d <- dim(X)

                    		
                  

                  

                    40
                    5x
                    
                      
  dl <- length(d)

                    		
                  

                  

                    41
                    5x
                    
                      
  if (dl < 2L)                               # Vector, maybe a time profile

                    		
                  

                  

                    42
                    !
                    
                      
    res <- if (nl < 2L) list(FUN(X, ...))

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    !
                    
                      
           else lapply(split(X, fac), FUN, ...)

                    		
                  

                  

                    44
                    
                    
                      
  else {                                     # Matrix or array

                    		
                  

                  

                    45
                    5x
                    
                      
    d2 <- prod(d[-oper])

                    		
                  

                  

                    46
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    47
                    5x
                    
                      
    newX <- if (oper == 1L) X

                    		
                  

                  

                    48
                    5x
                    
                      
            else aperm(X, c(oper, seq_len(dl)[-oper]))

                    		
                  

                  

                    49
                    5x
                    
                      
    dim(newX) <- c(d[oper], d2)

                    		
                  

                  

                    50
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    51
                    5x
                    
                      
    res <- vector("list", d2)

                    		
                  

                  

                    52
                    5x
                    
                      
    if (nl < 2L)

                    		
                  

                  

                    53
                    !
                    
                      
      for (i in 1L:d2)

                    		
                  

                  

                    54
                    !
                    
                      
        res[[i]] <- FUN(newX[, i], ...)

                    		
                  

                  

                    55
                    
                    
                      
    else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    56
                    5x
                    
                      
      for (i in 1L:d2)

                    		
                  

                  

                    57
                    261960x
                    
                      
        res[[i]] <- lapply(split(newX[, i], fac), FUN, ...)

                    		
                  

                  

                    58
                    5x
                    
                      
      res <- unlist(res, recursive = FALSE, use.names = FALSE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    59
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    60
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    61
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    62
                    5x
                    
                      
  dimres <- length(res[[1L]])

                    		
                  

                  

                    63
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    64
                    
                    
                      
  # Set dimensions. If FUN returns multiple values, FUN values are in the first

                    		
                  

                  

                    65
                    
                    
                      
  # dimension.

                    		
                  

                  

                    66
                    5x
                    
                      
  res <- unlist(res, recursive = FALSE, use.names = FALSE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    67
                    5x
                    
                      
  dims <- c(if(dimres > 1L) dimres, if (nl > 1L) nl, if (dl > 1L) d[-oper])

                    		
                  

                  

                    68
                    5x
                    
                      
  if (length(dims) > 1L)

                    		
                  

                  

                    69
                    5x
                    
                      
    dim(res) <- dims

                    		
                  

                  

                    70
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    71
                    5x
                    
                      
  if (dimres == 1L)

                    		
                  

                  

                    72
                    
                    
                      
    # Always return a list

                    		
                  

                  

                    73
                    3x
                    
                      
    list(res)

                    		
                  

                  

                    74
                    2x
                    
                      
  else if (dl < 2L && nl < 2L)

                    		
                  

                  

                    75
                    
                    
                      
    # Vector input, no factor, multiple FUN values

                    		
                  

                  

                    76
                    !
                    
                      
    as.list(res)

                    		
                  

                  

                    77
                    
                    
                      
  else

                    		
                  

                  

                    78
                    
                    
                      
    # Separate FUN values into list elements

                    		
                  

                  

                    79
                    2x
                    
                      
    asplit(res, 1L)

                    		
                  

                  

                    80
                    
                    
                      
}

#' Make a data.frame slimmer by shortening long strings. List elements are

.slim.data.frame <- function(df, width = 50L) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    90
                    27x

                    91
                    27x

                    92

                    99

.is_valid_name <- function(nm) {

.make_valid_name <- function(nm) {

.c_is_monotonic <- function(x, y) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    165
                    3x
                    
                      
  xlen <- length(x)

                    		
                  

                  

                    166
                    3x

                    !

                    !
                    
                      
    else !.near(x, y[1L]) && ((x < y[1L] && y[1L] < y[2L]) || (x > y[1L] && y[1L] > y[2L]))

                    3x

                    3x

    } else {

                    3x

    hierarchy = function(idx = 1L, total = 1L) {

    #'   method returns an axis which spans the range of indices given by the

                    		
                  

                  

                    247
                    
                    
                      
    #'   `rng` argument.

                    		
                  

                  

                    248
                    
                    
                      
    #'

                    		
                  

                  

                    249
                    
                    
                      
    #' @param name The name for the new axis. If an empty string is passed

                    		
                  

                  

                    250
                    
                    
                      
    #'   (default), will use the name of this axis.

                    		
                  

                  

                    251
                    
                    
                      
    #' @param rng The range of indices whose values from this axis to include in

                    		
                  

                  

                    252
                    
                    
                      
    #'   the returned axis. If the value of the argument is `NULL`, return a

                    		
                  

                  

                    253
                    
                    
                      
    #'   copy of the axis.

                    		
                  

                  

                    254
                    
                    
                      
    #' @return A new `CFAxisNumeric` instance covering the indicated range of

                    		
                  

                  

                    255
                    
                    
                      
    #'   indices. If the value of the argument `rng` is `NULL`, return a copy of

                    		
                  

                  

                    256
                    
                    
                      
    #'   `self` as the new axis.

                    		
                  

                  

                    257
                    
                    
                      
    subset = function(name = "", rng = NULL) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    258
                    4x
                    
                      
      if (is.null(rng))

                    		
                  

                  

                    259
                    !
                    
                      
        self$copy(name)

                    		
                  

                  

                    260
                    
                    
                      
      else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    261
                    4x
                    
                      
        rng <- as.integer(range(rng))

                    		
                  

                  

                    262
                    4x
                    
                      
        idx <- private$.tm$indexOf(seq(from = rng[1L], to = rng[2L], by = 1L))

                    		
                  

                  

                    263
                    4x
                    
                      
        newtm <- attr(idx, "CFTime")

                    		
                  

                  

                    264
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    265
                    4x
                    
                      
        if (self$has_resource) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    266
                    4x
                    
                      
          ax <- CFAxisTime$new(self$NCvar, values = newtm, start = private$.start_count$start + rng[1L] - 1L,

                    		
                  

                  

                    267
                    4x
                    
                      
                               count = rng[2L] - rng[1L] + 1L, attributes = self$attributes)

                    		
                  

                  

                    268
                    4x
                    
                      
          if (nzchar(name))

                    		
                  

                  

                    269
                    !
                    
                      
            ax$name <- name

                    		
                  

                  

                    270
                    
                    
                      
        } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    271
                    !
                    
                      
          if (!nzchar(name))

                    		
                  

                  

                    272
                    !
                    
                      
            name <- self$name

                    		
                  

                  

                    273
                    !
                    
                      
          ax <- CFAxisTime$new(name, values = newtm, attributes = self$attributes)

                    		
                  

                  

                    274
                    
                    
                      
        }

                    		
                  

                  

                    275
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    276
                    4x
                    
                      
        if (inherits(private$.bounds, "CFBounds"))

                    		
                  

                  

                    277
                    3x
                    
                      
          ax$bounds <- private$.bounds$subset(rng)

                    		
                  

                  

                    278
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    279
                    4x
                    
                      
        private$subset_coordinates(ax, rng)

                    		
                  

                  

                    280
                    4x
                    
                      
        ax

                    		
                  

                  

                    281
                    
                    
                      
      }

    #' @description Write the axis to a netCDF file, including its attributes.

                    		
                  

                  

                    285
                    
                    
                      
    #' If the calendar name is "gregorian", it will be set to the functionally

                    		
                  

                  

                    286
                    
                    
                      
    #' identical calendar "standard" as the former is deprecated.

                    		
                  

                  

                    287
                    
                    
                      
    #' @param nc The handle of the netCDF file opened for writing or a group in

                    		
                  

                  

                    288
                    
                    
                      
    #'   the netCDF file. If `NULL`, write to the file or group where the axis

                    		
                  

                  

                    289
                    
                    
                      
    #'   was read from (the file must have been opened for writing). If not

                    		
                  

                  

                    290
                    
                    
                      
    #'   `NULL`, the handle to a netCDF file or a group therein.

                    		
                  

                  

                    291
                    
                    
                      
    #' @return Self, invisibly.

                    		
                  

                  

                    292
                    
                    
                      
    write = function(nc = NULL) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    293
                    !
                    
                      
      time <- private$.tm

                    		
                  

                  

                    294
                    !
                    
                      
      if (time$cal$name == "gregorian")

                    		
                  

                  

                    295
                    !
                    
                      
        self$set_attribute("calendar", "NC_CHAR", "standard")

                    		
                  

                  

                    296
                    !
                    
                      
      super$write(nc)

                    		
                  

                  

                    297
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    298
                    !
                    
                      
      bnds <- time$get_bounds()

                    		
                  

                  

                    299
                    !
                    
                      
      if (!is.null(bnds)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    300
                    
                    
                      
        # Do we have to record did somewhere??

                    		
                  

                  

                    301
                    !
                    
                      
        dnm <- "nv"

                    		
                  

                  

                    302
                    !
                    
                      
        did <- try(RNetCDF::dim.def.nc(nc, dnm, 2L), silent = TRUE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    303
                    !
                    
                      
        if (inherits(did, "try-error")) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    304
                    !
                    
                      
          did <- RNetCDF::dim.inq.nc(nc, dnm)

                    		
                  

                  

                    305
                    !
                    
                      
          did <- if (did$length == 2L) did$id

                    		
                  

                  

                    306
                    
                    
                      
                 else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    307
                    !
                    
                      
                   dnm <- paste(sample(letters, 8, TRUE), collapse = "") # Random name

                    		
                  

                  

                    308
                    !
                    
                      
                   RNetCDF::dim.def.nc(nc, dnm, 2L)

                    		
                  

                  

                    309
                    
                    
                      
                 }

                    		
                  

                  

                    310
                    
                    
                      
        }

                    		
                  

                  

                    311
                    !
                    
                      
        nm <- if (inherits(time, "CFClimatology")) self$attribute("climatology") else self$attribute("bounds")

                    		
                  

                  

                    312
                    !
                    
                      
        RNetCDF::var.def.nc(nc, nm, "NC_DOUBLE", c(dnm, self$name))

                    		
                  

                  

                    313
                    !
                    
                      
        RNetCDF::var.put.nc(nc, nm, bnds)

                    		
                  

                  

                    314
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    315
                    
                    
                      
    }

      paste0('METHOD["Vertical Perspective",', .wkt2_id(9838), ']',

                    		
                  

                  

                    393
                    !
                    
                      
             ',PARAMETER["Latitude of topocentric origin",', lat0, ',', angle, ']',

                    		
                  

                  

                    394
                    !
                    
                      
             ',PARAMETER["Longitude of topocentric origin",', lon0, ',', angle, ']',

                    		
                  

                  

                    395
                    !
                    
                      
             ',PARAMETER["Viewpoint height",', h, ',', .wkt2_uom(9001), ']')

                    		
                  

                  

                    396
                    
                    
                      
    },

                    398
                    
                    
                      
    # === CRS objects ==========================================================

                    		
                  

                  

                    399
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    400
                    
                    
                      
    # This method creates an UOM WKT2 string from a specified UOM name. This is

                    		
                  

                  

                    401
                    
                    
                      
    # typically called to describe the UOM of CFVariable axes for the CS section

                    		
                  

                  

                    402
                    
                    
                      
    # of a full WKT2 string for a CFVariable instance.

                    		
                  

                  

                    403
                    
                    
                      
    # Known aliases (by the EPSG database) are interpreted correctly, with the

                    		
                  

                  

                    404
                    
                    
                      
    # resulting WKT2 string using the default name of the UOM. If no alias is

                    		
                  

                  

                    405
                    
                    
                      
    # found, the method returns an empty string, otherwise the WKT2 string.

                    		
                  

                  

                    406
                    
                    
                      
    # If argument `id` is `TRUE`, include an ID section, exclude otherwise.

                    		
                  

                  

                    407
                    
                    
                      
    uom = function(name, id = FALSE) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    408
                    1x
                    
                      
      if (name %in% c("degrees", "meters", "kilometers", "metres", "kilometres",

                    		
                  

                  

                    409
                    1x
                    
                      
                      "seconds", "minutes", "hours", "days", "months", "years"))

                    		
                  

                  

                    410
                    !
                    
                      
        name <- trimws(name, whitespace = "s")

                    		
                  

                  

                    411
                    1x
                    
                      
      details <- epsg_uom[epsg_uom$unit_of_meas_name == name, ]

                    		
                  

                  

                    412
                    !
                    
                      
      if (nrow(details)) .wkt2_uom(details$uom_code, id)

                    		
                  

                  

                    413
                    
                    
                      
      else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    414
                    1x
                    
                      
        details <- epsg_uom_alias[epsg_uom_alias$alias == name, ]

                    		
                  

                  

                    415
                    1x
                    
                      
        if (nrow(details)) .wkt2_uom(details$object_code, id)

                    		
                  

                  

                    416
                    !
                    
                      
        else return('')

                    		
                  

                  

                    417
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    418
                    
                    
                      
    },

                    		
                  

                  

                    419
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    420
                    
                    
                      
    # Create an ellipsoid WKT2 from attributes by finding an EPSG code by (1)

                    		
                  

                  

                    421
                    
                    
                      
    # name or (2) other attributes, or (3) otherwise a "manual" string from

                    		
                  

                  

                    422
                    
                    
                      
    # attributes, or (4) an empty string if no attributes are present, in that

                    		
                  

                  

                    423
                    
                    
                      
    # order. Note that the semi_major_axis, semi_minor_axis and earth_radius are

                    		
                  

                  

                    424
                    
                    
                      
    # required to be in meters, meaning that 9 EPSG ellipsoids cannot be

                    		
                  

                  

                    425
                    
                    
                      
    # represented through attributes.

                    		
                  

                  

                    426
                    
                    
                      
    ellipsoid = function() {

                    		
                  

                  

                    427
                    
                    
                      
      # (1) Find an EPSG code by name, set ellipsoid name otherwise

                    		
                  

                  

                    428
                    1x
                    
                      
      if (is.na(ell_name <- self$attribute("reference_ellipsoid_name")))

                    		
                  

                  

                    429
                    1x
                    
                      
        ell_name <- 'unknown'

                    		
                  

                  

                    430
                    
                    
                      
      else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    431
                    !
                    
                      
        epsg_code <- epsg_ell[epsg_ell$ellipsoid_name == ell_name, "ellipsoid_code"]

                    		
                  

                  

                    432
                    !
                    
                      
        if (length(epsg_code)) return(.wkt2_ellipsoid(epsg_code))

                    		
                  

                  

                    433
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    434
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    435
                    1x
                    
                      
      a <- self$attribute("semi_major_axis")

                    		
                  

                  

                    436
                    1x
                    
                      
      b <- self$attribute("semi_minor_axis")

                    		
                  

                  

                    437
                    1x
                    
                      
      invf <- self$attribute("inverse_flattening")

                    		
                  

                  

                    438
                    1x
                    
                      
      r <- self$attribute("earth_radius")

                    		
                  

                  

                    439
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    440
                    
                    
                      
      # (2) Find an EPSG code by set of attributes

                    		
                  

                  

                    441
                    1x
                    
                      
      details <- if (is.na(a)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    442
                    1x
                    
                      
        if (is.na(r)) data.frame()

                    		
                  

                  

                    443
                    !
                    
                      
        else epsg_ell[isTRUE(all.equal(epsg_ell$semi_major_axis, r)), ]

                    		
                  

                  

                    444
                    
                    
                      
      } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    445
                    !
                    
                      
        if (!is.na(invf))

                    		
                  

                  

                    446
                    !
                    
                      
          epsg_ell[isTRUE(all.equal(c(epsg_ell$semi_major_axis, epsg_ell$inv_flattening), c(a, invf))), ]

                    		
                  

                  

                    447
                    !
                    
                      
        else if (!is.na(b))

                    		
                  

                  

                    448
                    !
                    
                      
          epsg_ell[isTRUE(all.equal(c(epsg_ell$semi_major_axis, epsg_ell$semi_minor_axis), c(a, b))), ]

                    		
                  

                  

                    449
                    
                    
                      
        else

                    		
                  

                  

                    450
                    !
                    
                      
          epsg_ell[isTRUE(all.equal(c(epsg_ell$semi_major_axis, epsg_ell$semi_minor_axis), c(a, a))), ]

                    		
                  

                  

                    451
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    452
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    453
                    1x
                    
                      
      if (nrow(details) == 1L)

                    		
                  

                  

                    454
                    !
                    
                      
        .wkt2_ellipsoid(details$ellipsoid_code)

                    		
                  

                  

                    455
                    
                    
                      
      else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    456
                    
                    
                      
        # (3) Manual WKT

                    		
                  

                  

                    457
                    1x
                    
                      
        uom <- .wkt2_uom(9001L) # CF only supports meter uom

                    		
                  

                  

                    458
                    1x
                    
                      
        if (!is.na(a)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    459
                    !
                    
                      
          if (is.na(invf))

                    		
                  

                  

                    460
                    !
                    
                      
            invf <- if (is.na(b)) 0 else a / (a - b)

                    		
                  

                  

                    461
                    !
                    
                      
          paste0('ELLIPSOID["', ell_name, '",', a, ',', invf, ',', uom, ']')

                    		
                  

                  

                    462
                    1x
                    
                      
        } else if (!is.na(r)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    463
                    !
                    
                      
          paste0('ELLIPSOID["', ell_name, '",', r, ',0,', uom, ']')

                    		
                  

                  

                    464
                    1x
                    
                      
        } else '' # (4) fail

                    		
                  

                  

                    465
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    466
                    
                    
                      
    },

                    		
                  

                  

                    467
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    468
                    
                    
                      
    # Create a prime meridian WKT2 from attributes by finding an EPSG code by

                    		
                  

                  

                    469
                    
                    
                      
    # name or longitude, or an empty string if no attributes are present.

                    		
                  

                  

                    470
                    
                    
                      
    # The return value is a list with two elements: WKT2 holds the WKT2 string,

                    		
                  

                  

                    471
                    
                    
                      
    # ANGLEUNIT holds the EPSG code of the UOM.

                    		
                  

                  

                    472
                    
                    
                      
    prime_meridian = function() {

                    		
                  

                  

                    473
                    !
                    
                      
      details <- if (!is.na(pm <- self$attribute("prime_meridian_name"))) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    474
                    !
                    
                      
        epsg_pm[epsg_pm$prime_meridian_name == pm, ]

                    		
                  

                  

                    475
                    !
                    
                      
      } else if (!is.na(lon <- self$attribute("longitude_of_prime_meridian"))) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    476
                    !
                    
                      
        epsg_pm[isTRUE(all.equal(epsg_pm$greenwich_longitude, lon)), ]

                    		
                  

                  

                    477
                    !
                    
                      
      } else data.frame()

                    		
                  

                  

                    478
                    !
                    
                      
      if (nrow(details)) list(WKT2 = .wkt2_pm(details$prime_meridian_code), ANGLEUNIT = details$uom_code)

                    		
                  

                  

                    479
                    !
                    
                      
      else list(WKT2 = '', ANGLEUNIT = 9102)

                    		
                  

                  

                    480
                    
                    
                      
    },

                    		
                  

                  

                    481
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    482
                    
                    
                      
    # Return the EPSG code of the ANGLEUNIT of the prime meridian used by the

                    		
                  

                  

                    483
                    
                    
                      
    # geodetic datum or its ensemble.

                    		
                  

                  

                    484
                    
                    
                      
    datum_angleunit = function(epsg_code) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    485
                    1x
                    
                      
      datum <- epsg_datum[epsg_datum$datum_code == epsg_code, ]

                    		
                  

                  

                    486
                    1x
                    
                      
      if (datum$datum_type == "vertical")

                    		
                  

                  

                    487
                    !
                    
                      
        stop("Only call this function for a geodetic datum.")

                    		
                  

                  

                    488
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    489
                    1x
                    
                      
      if (datum$datum_type == "ensemble") {

                    		
                  

                  

                    490
                    1x
                    
                      
        members <- epsg_datum_ensemble[epsg_datum_ensemble$datum_ensemble_code == datum$datum_code, ]

                    		
                  

                  

                    491
                    1x
                    
                      
        datum <- epsg_datum[epsg_datum$datum_code == members$member_code[1L], ]

                    		
                  

                  

                    492
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    493
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    494
                    1x
                    
                      
      epsg_pm[epsg_pm$prime_meridian_code == datum$prime_meridian_code[1L], "uom_code"]

                    		
                  

                  

                    495
                    
                    
                      
    },

                    		
                  

                  

                    496
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    497
                    
                    
                      
    # Create a geodetic datum WKT2 from attributes by finding an EPSG code by

                    		
                  

                  

                    498
                    
                    
                      
    # name. If there is no attribute to name the datum or the name is not

                    		
                  

                  

                    499
                    
                    
                      
    # present in the EPSG database, an ellipsoid is sought for. If an ellipsoid

                    		
                  

                  

                    500
                    
                    
                      
    # is found, a "manual" WKT is made, possibly with a prime meridian if

                    		
                  

                  

                    501
                    
                    
                      
    # specified. Otherwise a WGS84 datum is returned, as the default. Note that

                    		
                  

                  

                    502
                    
                    
                      
    # this procedure extends the CF guidance, which requires that any name be

                    		
                  

                  

                    503
                    
                    
                      
    # a valid EPSG database datum name.

                    		
                  

                  

                    504
                    
                    
                      
    # The return value is a list with two elements: WKT2 holds the WKT2 string,

                    		
                  

                  

                    505
                    
                    
                      
    # ANGLEUNIT holds the EPSG code of the UOM used by the datum

                    		
                  

                  

                    506
                    
                    
                      
    datum_geo = function() {

                    		
                  

                  

                    507
                    1x
                    
                      
      dtm_name <- self$attribute("horizontal_datum_name")

                    		
                  

                  

                    508
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    509
                    
                    
                      
      # EPSG datum from attribute name

                    		
                  

                  

                    510
                    1x
                    
                      
      if (!is.na(dtm_name)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    511
                    !
                    
                      
        dtm_code <- epsg_datum[epsg_datum$cf_name == dtm_name, "datum_code"]

                    		
                  

                  

                    512
                    !
                    
                      
        if (!length(dtm_code))

                    		
                  

                  

                    513
                    !
                    
                      
          dtm_code <- epsg_datum[epsg_datum$datum_name == dtm_name, "datum_code"]

                    		
                  

                  

                    514
                    !
                    
                      
        if (length(dtm_code))

                    		
                  

                  

                    515
                    !
                    
                      
          return(list(source = "EPSG", WKT2 = .wkt2_datum_geo(dtm_code), ANGLEUNIT = private$datum_angleunit(dtm_code)))

                    		
                  

                  

                    516
                    1x
                    
                      
      } else dtm_name <- 'unknown'

                    		
                  

                  

                    517
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    518
                    
                    
                      
      # Manual

                    		
                  

                  

                    519
                    1x
                    
                      
      ellipsoid <- private$ellipsoid()

                    		
                  

                  

                    520
                    1x
                    
                      
      if (nzchar(ellipsoid)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    521
                    !
                    
                      
        pm <- private$prime_meridian()

                    		
                  

                  

                    522
                    !
                    
                      
        if (nzchar(pm$WKT2)) pm$WKT2 <- paste0(',', pm$WKT2)

                    		
                  

                  

                    523
                    !
                    
                      
        list(source = "manual", WKT2 = paste0('DATUM["', dtm_name, '",', ellipsoid, ']', pm$WKT2), ANGLEUNIT = pm$ANGLEUNIT)

                    		
                  

                  

                    524
                    
                    
                      
      } else

                    		
                  

                  

                    525
                    1x
                    
                      
        list(source = "default", WKT2 = .wkt2_datum_geo(6326L), ANGLEUNIT = private$datum_angleunit(6326L))

                    		
                  

                  

                    526
                    
                    
                      
    },

                    		
                  

                  

                    527
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    528

      details <- epsg_datum[epsg_datum$datum_name == name, ]

                    		
                  

                  

                    530
                    !

                    531

        .wkt2_datum_vert(details$datum_code)

                    		
                  

                  

                    532
                    !
                    
                      
      else paste0('VDATUM["', name, '"]')

    },

                    541
                    
                    
                      
    # Either the epsg_code argument or the name argument has to be specified. If

                    		
                  

                  

                    542
                    
                    
                      
    # both are specified, the name argument will be ignored.

                    		
                  

                  

                    543
