    geo_crs = function(epsg_code = NULL, name = NULL) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    549
                    !
                    
                      
      if (is.null(epsg_code)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    550
                    !
                    
                      
        details <- epsg_geo_crs[epsg_geo_crs$coord_ref_sys_name == name, ]

                    		
                  

                  

                    551
                    !
                    
                      
        if (!nrow(details)) return('')

                    		
                  

                  

                    552
                    !
                    
                      
        if (nrow(details) > 1L) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    553
                    !
                    
                      
          if (private$.grid_mapping_name == "latitude_longitude")

                    		
                  

                  

                    554
                    !
                    
                      
            details <- details[details$coord_ref_sys_kind == "geographic 2D", ]

                    		
                  

                  

                    555
                    !
                    
                      
          else return('')

                    		
                  

                  

                    556
                    
                    
                      
        }

                    		
                  

                  

                    557
                    !
                    
                      
        epsg_code <- details$coord_ref_sys_code

                    		
                  

                  

                    558
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    559
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    560
                    !
                    
                      
      .wkt2_crs_geo(epsg_code)

                    		
                  

                  

                    561
                    
                    
                      
    },

                    		
                  

                  

                    562
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    563
                    
                    
                      
    # Either the epsg_code argument or the name argument has to be specified. If

                    		
                  

                  

                    564
                    
                    
                      
    # both are specified, the name argument will be ignored.

                    		
                  

                  

                    565
                    
                    
                      
    # The arguments may refer to a projected CRS or a compound CRS.

                    		
                  

                  

                    566

    # A PROJCRS always has a base_crs_code, projection_conv_code and coord_sys_code

    proj_crs = function(epsg_code = NULL, name = NULL) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    569
                    !
                    
                      
      if (!is.null(epsg_code)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    570
                    !
                    
                      
        details <- epsg_proj_crs[epsg_proj_crs$coord_ref_sys_code == epsg_code, ]

                    		
                  

                  

                    571
                    !
                    
                      
        if (nrow(details) == 0L) return(private$cmpd_crs(epsg_code, name))

                    		
                  

                  

                    572
                    !
                    
                      
      } else if (!is.null(name)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    573
                    !
                    
                      
        details <- epsg_proj_crs[epsg_proj_crs$coord_ref_sys_name == name, ]

                    		
                  

                  

                    574
                    !
                    
                      
        if (nrow(details) == 0L)  return(private$cmpd_crs(epsg_code, name))

                    		
                  

                  

                    575
                    !
                    
                      
        if (nrow(details) > 1L) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    576
                    !
                    
                      
          warning(paste0("Multiple CRS entries found for '", name, "'. Using the first entry."))

                    		
                  

                  

                    577
                    !
                    
                      
          details <- details[1L, ]

                    		
                  

                  

                    578
                    
                    
                      
        }

                    		
                  

                  

                    579
                    !
                    
                      
      } else return('')

                    		
                  

                  

                    580
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    581
                    !
                    
                      
      paste0('PROJCRS["', details$coord_ref_sys_name, '",',

                    		
                  

                  

                    582
                    !
                    
                      
             .wkt2_crs_base(details$base_crs_code), ',',

                    		
                  

                  

                    583
                    !
                    
                      
             .wkt2_conversion(details$projection_conv_code), ',',

                    		
                  

                  

                    584
                    !
                    
                      
             private$coordsys(details$coord_sys_code), ',',

                    		
                  

                  

                    585
                    !
                    
                      
             .wkt2_id(details$coord_ref_sys_code), ']')

                    		
                  

                  

                    586
                    
                    
                      
    },

    vert_crs = function(epsg_code) {

    # Either the epsg_code argument or the name argument has to be specified. If

    cmpd_crs = function(epsg_code = NULL, name = NULL) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    595
                    !
                    
                      
      if (is.null(epsg_code)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    596

      }

                    603
                    
                    
                      
  ),

                    		
                  

                  

                    604
                    
                    
                      
  public = list(

                    		
                  

                  

                    605
                    
                    
                      
    #' @description Create a new instance of this class.

                    		
                  

                  

                    606
                    
                    
                      
    #'

                    		
                  

                  

                    607
                    
                    
                      
    #'   Note that when a new grid mapping object is created (as opposed to

                    		
                  

                  

                    608
                    
                    
                      
    #'   reading from a netCDF resource), only the `grid_mapping_name` attribute

                    		
                  

                  

                    609
                    
                    
                      
    #'   will be set. The caller must set all other parameters through their

                    		
                  

                  

                    610
                    
                    
                      
    #'   respective attributes, following the CF Metadata Conventions.

                    		
                  

                  

                    611
                    
                    
                      
    #' @param var When creating a new grid mapping object, the name of the

                    		
                  

                  

                    612
                    
                    
                      
    #'   object. When reading from a netCDF resource, the netCDF variable that

                    		
                  

                  

                    613
                    
                    
                      
    #'   describes this instance.

                    		
                  

                  

                    614
                    
                    
                      
    #' @param grid_mapping_name Optional. When creating a new grid mapping

                    		
                  

                  

                    615
                    
                    
                      
    #'   object, the formal name of the grid mapping, as specified in the CF

                    		
                  

                  

                    616
                    
                    
                      
    #'   Metadata Conventions. This value is stored in the new object as

                    		
                  

                  

                    617
                    
                    
                      
    #'   attribute "grid_mapping_name". Ignored when argument `var` is a NC

                    		
                  

                  

                    618
                    
                    
                      
    #'   object.

                    		
                  

                  

                    619
                    
                    
                      
    initialize = function(var, grid_mapping_name) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    620
                    6x
                    
                      
      super$initialize(var)

                    		
                  

                  

                    621
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    622
                    6x
                    
                      
      if (is.character(var)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    623
                    1x
                    
                      
        if (missing(grid_mapping_name))

                    		
                  

                  

                    624
                    
                    
                      
          stop("Must provide the `grid_mapping_name` argument when creating a new grid mapping object.", call. = FALSE) # nocov

                    		
                  

                  

                    625
                    1x
                    
                      
        grid_mapping_name <- grid_mapping_name[1L]

                    		
                  

                  

                    626
                    1x
                    
                      
        if (!(grid_mapping_name %in% CRS_names))

                    		
                  

                  

                    627

    wkt2 = function(axis_info) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    655
                    1x

# Helper function

                    		
                  

                  

                    749
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    750
                    
                    
                      
# Return the axis information from a `CFVariable` object to construct a

                    		
                  

                  

                    751
                    
                    
                      
# WKT2 string of the CRS of this variable. Returns a list with relevant

                    		
                  

                  

                    752
                    
                    
                      
# information. In the EPSG database, X and Y UOMs are always the same. Hence

                    		
                  

                  

                    753
                    
                    
                      
# only one UOM is reported back. Furthermore, axis order is considered important

                    		
                  

                  

                    754
                    
                    
                      
# only in the context of providing coordinated tuples to a coordinate

                    		
                  

                  

                    755
                    
                    
                      
# transformation engine, something this package is not concerned with.

                    		
                  

                  

                    756
                    
                    
                      
# Consequently, axis order is always reported as the standard X,Y. R packages

                    		
                  

                  

                    757
                    
                    
                      
# like terra and stars deal with the idiosyncracies of R arrays. This has been

                    		
                  

                  

                    758
                    
                    
                      
# tested with the results of [CFVariable] functions. This function may be extended

                    		
                  

                  

                    759
                    
                    
                      
# in the future to inject more intelligence into the WKT2 strings produced.

                    		
                  

                  

                    760
                    
                    
                      
# Currently it just returns the "units" string of the X axis (the Y axis has the

                    		
                  

                  

                    761
                    
                    
                      
# same unit), and the Z axis, if present, in a list.

                    		
                  

                  

                    762
                    
                    
                      
.wkt2_axis_info <- function(obj) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    763
                    
                    
                      
  # Horizontal axes unit

                    		
                  

                  

                    764
                    1x
                    
                      
  x_attributes <- c("projection_x_coordinate", "grid_longitude", "projection_x_angular_coordinate")

                    		
                  

                  

                    765
                    1x
                    
                      
  ax <- lapply(obj$axes, function(x) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    766
                    1x
                    
                      
    if (x$attribute("standard_name") %in% x_attributes) x

                    		
                  

                  

                    767
                    
                    
                      
  })

                    		
                  

                  

                    768
                    1x
                    
                      
  ax <- ax[lengths(ax) > 0L]

                    		
                  

                  

                    769
                    1x
                    
                      
  horz <- if (length(ax) > 0L) list(LENGTHUNIT = ax[[1L]]$attribute("units"))

                    		
                  

                  

                    770
                    1x
                    
                      
  else list()

                    		
                  

                  

                    771
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    772
                    
                    
                      
  # Vertical axes unit

                    		
                  

                  

                    773
                    1x
                    
                      
  z <- sapply(obj$axes, function(x) x$orientation)

                    		
                  

                  

                    774
                    1x
                    
                      
  ndx <- which(z == "Z")

                    		
                  

                  

                    775
                    1x
                    
                      
  vert <- if (length(ndx)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    776
                    1x
                    
                      
    z <- obj$axes[[ndx]]

                    		
                  

                  

                    777
                    1x
                    
                      
    if (inherits(z, "CFAxis"))

                    		
                  

                  

                    778
                    1x
                    
                      
      list(VERTINFO = c(z$attribute("standard_name"), z$attribute("positive"), z$attribute("units")))

                    		
                  

                  

                    779
                    !
                    
                      
    else list()

                    		
                  

                  

                    780
                    1x
                    
                      
  } else list()

                    		
                  

                  

                    781
                    1x
                    
                      
  c(horz, vert)

                    		
                  

                  

                    782
                    
                    
                      
}

                    		
                  

                
              

            

            

              

                
                  

                    1
                    
                    
                      
#' Latitude CF axis object

.check_latitude_domain <- function(crds) {

                    !

#' Operations on CFVariable objects

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
#' Basic arithmetic, mathematical and logical operations can be applied on the

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
#' data of [CFVariable] objects having a suitable data type, specifically the

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#' base R functions from the Ops and Math groups of the S3 [groupGeneric]

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#' functions.

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#' The functions always return a new `CFVariable` object. Functions can thus be

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#' concatenated to create more complex expressions. The data type of the new

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
#' object is determined by the base R function; its name is concatenated from

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#' the names in the argument object(s).

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
#' For the Ops functions with two arguments, if both arguments are a

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
#' `CFVariable` object they have to be compatible: same shape, axis coordinate

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
#' values and coordinate reference system. The resulting `CFVariable` object

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
#' will use the same axes as the `CFVariable` object(s) used as argument.

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      
#' The attributes of the resulting `CFVariable` object should be updated to

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    
                    
                      
#' reflect its contents, in particular the "name", "long_name", "standard_name"

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      
#' and "units" attributes. Attributes are not copied over from the `CFVariable`

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    
                    
                      
#' objects in the arguments.

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    
                    
                      
#' @param e1,e2 `CFVariable` objects, or a single numeric value.

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    
                    
                      
#' @return A new `CFVariable` object. The object will have the same coordinate

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    
                    
                      
#'   space as the `CFVariable` object used as argument. Arguments are not copied

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    
                    
                      
#'   and the new object will only have the "actual_range" attribute set.

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    
                    
                      
#'   Results that are logical (see the examples) are stored using the `NC_SHORT`

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    
                    
                      
#'   data type because netCDF does not have a native logical data type.

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    
                    
                      
#' @rdname arrayOps

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    
                    
                      
#' @examples

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    
                    
                      
#' fn <- system.file("extdata", "ERA5land_Rwanda_20160101.nc", package = "ncdfCF")

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    
                    
                      
#' ds <- open_ncdf(fn)

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    
                    
                      
#' # Temperature data in K

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    
                    
                      
#' t2m <- ds[["t2m"]]

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    40
                    
                    
                      
#' # Convert to degrees_Celsius

                    		
                  

                  

                    41
                    
                    
                      
#' t2mC <- t2m - 273.15

                    		
                  

                  

                    42
                    
                    
                      
#' t2mC$name <- "t2m_Celsius"

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    
                    
                      
#' t2mC$set_attribute("units", "NC_CHAR", "degrees_Celsius")

                    		
                  

                  

                    44
                    
                    
                      
#' t2mC

                    		
                  

                  

                    45
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    46
                    
                    
                      
#' hot <- t2mC > 20

                    		
                  

                  

                    47
                    
                    
                      
#' hot$name <- "t2m_Celsius_over_20"

                    		
                  

                  

                    48
                    
                    
                      
#' hot$set_attribute("long_name", "NC_CHAR", "Flag to indicate where temperature is 20C or hotter")

#' hot

Ops.CFVariable <- function(e1, e2) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    53
                    4x
                    
                      
  fun <- match.fun(.Generic)

                    		
                  

                  

                    54
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    55
                    4x
                    
                      
  if (inherits(e1, "CFVariable")) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    56
                    4x
                    
                      
    d1 <- e1$read_data()

                    4x

                    58
                    4x
                    
                      
    crs <- e1$crs

                    4x

  } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    61
                    !

                    62
                    !
                    
                      
    name <- paste0("x", e1)

                    		
                  

                  

                    63

                    64
                    4x
                    
                      
  if (missing(e2)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    65

                    66
                    !
                    
                      
    res <- fun(d1)

                    		
                  

                  

                    67
                    !
                    
                      
    name <- paste("inv", name, sep = "_")

                    		
                  

                  

                    68
                    
                    
                      
  } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    69
                    4x
                    
                      
    if (inherits(e2, "CFVariable")) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    70
                    !
                    
                      
      if (inherits(e1, "CFVariable")) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    71
                    !
                    
                      
        if (!e1$is_coincident(e2))

                    		
                  

                  

                    72
                    !
                    
                      
          stop("CFVariable arguments are not coincident.", call. = FALSE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    73
                    
                    
                      
      } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    74

        crs <- e2$crs

                    		
                  

                  

                    75

                    77

      d2 <- e2$read_data()

                    		
                  

                  

                    78
                    !
                    
                      
      name <- paste(name, e2$name, sep = "_")

                    		
                  

                  

                    79
                    
                    
                      
    } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    80
                    4x
                    
                      
      d2 <- e2

                    		
                  

                  

                    81
                    4x
                    
                      
      name <- paste(name, e2, sep = "_")

                    		
                  

                  

                    82

    res <- fun(d1, d2)

                    		
                  

                  

                    84

                    87
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    88

  v$crs <- crs

                    4x

}

                    1
                    
                    
                      
#' CF Standard names table

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
#' @description The CF Metadata Conventions define a large number of standard

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
#'   names for physical parameters, including axes and data variables. This

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#'   class accesses the standard names table. For each of the entries in the

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#'   table two properties are provided: the canonical unit and a description.

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#'   These properties are retrieved when searching for a given name.

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#'   Access to this class is through the `CF` environment. Use the

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
#'   `CF$standard_names$find("name_of_interest")` method to access a particular

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#'   standard name. It is strongly recommended not to instantiate this class

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
#'   manually as that may introduce problems with accessing the underlying XML

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
#'   file.

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
#'   The XML table is retrieved from the CF Metadata Conventions web site

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
#'   [here](https://cfconventions.org/vocabularies.html) and stored locally in

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
#'   the cache of the `ncdfCF` package. A check is performed periodically for an

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      
#'   updated version, which will then be downloaded automatically. The frequency

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    
                    
                      
#'   of the update check can be controlled with the

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      
#'   `CF.options$cache_stale_days` option.

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    
                    
                      
#' @references

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    
                    
                      
#' https://cfconventions.org/cf-conventions/cf-conventions.html#standard-name

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    
                    
                      
#' @docType class

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    
                    
                      
CFStandardNames <- R6::R6Class("CFStandardNames",

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    
                    
                      
  private = list(

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    
                    
                      
    # The `xml_document` that contains all the names.

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    
                    
                      
    names = NULL,

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    
                    
                      
    # Open the standard names table in XML format. Returns the XML document as

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    
                    
                      
    # a `xml_document` produced by package `xml2` (which must be installed). If

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    
                    
                      
    # there is any error, returns `NULL`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    
                    
                      
    # The XML file is stored locally in the package cache. Periodically there

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    
                    
                      
    # will be a check to see if a new version of the table is available.

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    
                    
                      
    retrieve = function() {

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    !
                    
                      
      if (!requireNamespace("xml2")) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    !
                    
                      
        stop("Must install package `xml2` to use the standard names table", call. = FALSE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    40
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    41
                    !
                    
                      
      res <- try({

                    		
                  

                  

                    42
                    !
                    
                      
        src <- "https://cfconventions.org/Data/cf-standard-names/current/src/cf-standard-name-table.xml"

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    !
                    
                      
        cache <- tools::R_user_dir("ncdfCF", "cache")

                    		
                  

                  

                    44
                    !
                    
                      
        if (!dir.exists(cache)) dir.create(cache, mode = "755")

                    		
                  

                  

                    45
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    46
                    !
                    
                      
        fn <- file.path(cache, "cf-standard-name-table.xml")

                    		
                  

                  

                    47
                    !
                    
                      
        if (file.exists(fn)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    48
                    !
                    
                      
          snx <- xml2::read_xml(fn)

                    		
                  

                  

                    49
                    !
                    
                      
          if (file.mtime(fn) < Sys.time() - CF.options$cache_stale_days * 86400) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    50
                    
                    
                      
            # Check if there is an update to the standard_name table

                    		
                  

                  

                    51
                    !
                    
                      
            con <- url(src)

                    		
                  

                  

                    52
                    !
                    
                      
            header <- readLines(con, n = 3)  # read first 3 lines only

                    		
                  

                  

                    53
                    !
                    
                      
            close(con)

                    		
                  

                  

                    54
                    !
                    
                      
            remote_version <- as.integer(regmatches(header[3], regexpr("[0-9]+", header[3])))

                    		
                  

                  

                    55
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    56
                    !
                    
                      
            local_version <- xml2::xml_integer(xml2::xml_find_first(snx, "/standard_name_table/version_number"))

                    		
                  

                  

                    57
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    58
                    !
                    
                      
            if (local_version < remote_version) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    59
                    !
                    
                      
              snx <- NULL # Drop the reference to the file so it can be overwritten

                    		
                  

                  

                    60
                    !
                    
                      
              xml2::download_xml(src, fn)

                    		
                  

                  

                    61
                    !
                    
                      
              snx <- xml2::read_xml(fn)

                    		
                  

                  

                    62
                    !
                    
                      
            } else Sys.setFileTime(fn, Sys.time()) # Reset the clock for checking

                    		
                  

                  

                    63
                    
                    
                      
          }

                    		
                  

                  

                    64
                    
                    
                      
        } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    65
                    !
                    
                      
          xml2::download_xml(src, fn)

                    		
                  

                  

                    66
                    !
                    
                      
          snx <- xml2::read_xml(fn)

                    		
                  

                  

                    67
                    
                    
                      
        }

                    		
                  

                  

                    68
                    !
                    
                      
        snx

                    		
                  

                  

                    69
                    !
                    
                      
      }, silent = TRUE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    70
                    !
                    
                      
      private$names <- if (inherits(res, "try-error")) NULL else res

                    		
                  

                  

                    71
                    !
                    
                      
      invisible(self)

                    		
                  

                  

                    72
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    73
                    
                    
                      
  ),

                    		
                  

                  

                    74
                    
                    
                      
  public = list(

                    		
                  

                  

                    75
                    
                    
                      
    #' @description Initialize an instance of this class. This is done

                    		
                  

                  

                    76
                    
                    
                      
    #'   automatically when the package is loaded.

                    		
                  

                  

                    77
                    
                    
                      
    initialize = function() {

                    		
                  

                  

                    78
                    
                    
                      
      # Empty function for quick start-up.

                    		
                  

                  

                    79
                    
                    
                      
    },

                    		
                  

                  

                    80
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    81
                    
                    
                      
    #' @description Print the version number of the standard names table in use,

    #' if it is loaded. The table is loaded automatically when it is first used.

    #' @description Retrieve the information on the specified names.

    #' @param names A character vector with the names to search the standard

                    		
                  

                  

                    93
                    
                    
                      
    #'   names table for.

    #' @return If an entry with a value in `names` is found, returns a

                    		
                  

                  

                    95
                    
                    
                      
    #'   `data.frame` with with with the canonical units and a description of

                    		
                  

                  

                    96
                    
                    
                      
    #'   the name. If no `names` are found in the table `NULL` is returned.

                    		
                  

                  

                    97
                    
                    
                      
    find = function(names) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    98
                    !
                    
                      
      if (is.null(private$names)) private$retrieve()

                    		
                  

                  

                    99
                    !
                    
                      
      if (is.null(private$names))

                    		
                  

                  

                    100
                    !
                    
                      
        stop("Standard names table is not available", call. = FALSE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    101
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    102
                    !
                    
                      
      xp <- paste0("//entry[@id='", names, "']")

                    		
                  

                  

                    103
                    !
                    
                      
      nodes <- lapply(xp, function(nm) xml2::xml_find_first(private$names, nm))

                    		
                  

                  

                    104
                    !
                    
                      
      found <- which(sapply(nodes, class) == "xml_node")

                    		
                  

                  

                    105
                    !
                    
                      
      if (length(found)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    106
                    !
                    
                      
        nodes <- nodes[found]

                    		
                  

                  

                    107
                    !
                    
                      
        cu <- sapply(nodes, function(n) xml2::xml_text(xml2::xml_find_first(n, "canonical_units")))

                    		
                  

                  

                    108
                    !
                    
                      
        desc <- sapply(nodes, function(n) xml2::xml_text(xml2::xml_find_first(n, "description")))

                    		
                  

                  

                    109
                    !
                    
                      
        data.frame(name = names[found], units = cu, description = desc)

                    		
                  

                  

                    110
                    !
                    
                      
      } else NULL

                    		
                  

                  

                    111
                    
                    
                      
    },

                    		
                  

                  

                    112
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    113
                    
                    
                      
    #' @description Load the standard names table so that it's contents may be

                    		
                  

                  

                    114
                    
                    
                      
    #' used in display and analysis. Note that the table may be downloaded

                    		
                  

                  

                    115
                    
                    
                      
    #' (4.3MB at version 91) if not available or stale.

                    		
                  

                  

                    116
                    
                    
                      
    #' @return Self, invisibly.

                    		
                  

                  

                    117
                    
                    
                      
    load = function() {

                    		
                  

                  

                    118
                    !
                    
                      
      private$retrieve()

                    		
                  

                  

                    119
                    !
                    
                      
      invisible(self)

                    		
                  

                  

                    120
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    121
                    
                    
                      
  ),

                    		
                  

                  

                    122
                    
                    
                      
  active = list(

                    		
                  

                  

                    123
                    
                    
                      
    #' @field is_loaded (read-only) Flag to determine if the standard names

                    		
                  

                  

                    124
                    
                    
                      
    #'   table is available.

                    		
                  

                  

                    125
                    
                    
                      
    is_loaded = function(value) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    126
                    !
                    
                      
      if (missing(value))

                    		
                  

                  

                    127
                    !
                    
                      
        !is.null(names)

                    		
                  

                  

                    128
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    129
                    
                    
                      
  )

                    		
                  

                  

                    130
                    
                    
                      
)

                    		
                  

                
              

            

            

              

                
                  

                    1
                    
                    
                      
#' Create an axis

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
#' With this method you can create an axis to use with new [CFVariable]

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
#' instances. Depending on the `orientation` argument and the type of the

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#' `values` argument an instance of a class descending from [CFAxis] will be

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#' returned.

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#' There are several restrictions on the combination of `orientation` and

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#' `values` arguments. Longitude, latitude and depth axes (`orientation` of "X",

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
#' "Y" or "Z") must have numeric `values`. For a time axis (`orientation` of

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#' "T") the `values` argument must be an instance of `CFTime` or

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
#' `CFClimatology`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
#' @param name Name of the axis.

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
#' @param orientation The orientation of the axis. Must be one of "X", "Y", "Z",

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
#'   or "T" for longitude, latitude, height or depth, and time axes,

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
#'   respectively. For any other axis, indicate an empty string ""

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      
#' @param values The coordinate values. In the case of an axis with `orientation

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    
                    
                      
#'   = "T"` this must be a `CFTime` or `CFClimatology` instance.

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      
#' @param bounds The boundary values of the coordinates, or `NULL` if not

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    
                    
                      
#'   available.

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    
                    
                      
#' @param attributes `data.frame` with the attributes of the axis to create.

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    
                    
                      
#'   Depending on which axis is created one or more attributes may be added or

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    
                    
                      
#'   amended.

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    
                    
                      
#' @seealso [makeLongitudeAxis()], [makeLatitudeAxis()], [makeTimeAxis()],

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    
                    
                      
#'   [makeDiscreteAxis()]

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    
                    
                      
#' @return An instance of a class descending from [CFAxis].

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    
                    
                      
makeAxis <- function(name, orientation, values, bounds = NULL, attributes = NULL) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    
                    
                      
  # FIXME: range check in addition to orientation

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    !
                    
                      
  if (orientation == "X") makeLongitudeAxis(name, values, bounds, attributes)

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    !
                    
                      
  else if (orientation == "Y") makeLatitudeAxis(name, values, bounds, attributes)

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    !
                    
                      
  else if (orientation == "Z") makeVerticalAxis(name, values, bounds, attributes)

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    !
                    
                      
  else if (orientation == "T") makeTimeAxis(name, values, attributes)

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    !
                    
                      
  else if (orientation == "") {

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    !
                    
                      
    if (is.numeric(values)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    
                    
                      
      # Check if we have a potential longitude or latitude axis

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    !
                    
                      
      if (tolower(name) %in% c("longitude", "lon") && .check_longitude_domain(values))

                    		
                  

                  

                    40
                    !
                    
                      
        makeLongitudeAxis(name, values, bounds, attributes)

                    		
                  

                  

                    41
                    !
                    
                      
      else if (tolower(name) %in% c("latitude", "lat") && .check_latitude_domain(values))

                    		
                  

                  

                    42
                    !
                    
                      
        makeLatitudeAxis(name, values, bounds, attributes)

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    
                    
                      
      else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    44
                    
                    
                      
        # Make a generic axis

                    		
                  

                  

                    45
                    !
                    
                      
        axis <- CFAxisNumeric$new(name, values = values, attributes = attributes)

                    		
                  

                  

                    46
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    47
                    !
                    
                      
        if (!is.null(bounds)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    48
                    !
                    
                      
          nm <- paste0(name, "_bnds")

                    		
                  

                  

                    49
                    !
                    
                      
          axis$bounds <- CFBounds$new(nm, bounds)

                    		
                  

                  

                    50
                    !
                    
                      
          axis$set_attribute("bounds", "NC_CHAR", nm)

                    		
                  

                  

                    51
                    
                    
                      
        }

                    		
                  

                  

                    52
                    !
                    
                      
        axis

                    		
                  

                  

                    53
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    54
                    !
                    
                      
    } else if (is.character(values)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    55
                    !
                    
                      
      axis <- CFAxisCharacter$new(name, values = values, attributes = attributes)

                    		
                  

                  

                    56
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    57
                    !
                    
                      
  } else stop("Bad `orientation` value for axis creation.", call. = FALSE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    58
                    
                    
                      
}

                    		
                  

                  

                    59
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    60
                    
                    
                      
#' Create a longitude axis

                    		
                  

                  

                    61

                    62

#' @param values The coordinate values.

#' @param bounds The bounds of the coordinate values, or `NULL` if not

                    		
                  

                  

                    68
                    
                    
                      
#'   available.

                    		
                  

                  

                    69
                    
                    
                      
#' @param attributes `data.frame` with the attributes of the axis to create.

                    		
                  

                  

                    70
                    
                    
                      
#'   Attributes "standard_name", "units", "actual_range" and "axis" will be set

                    		
                  

                  

                    71

                    74

                    75
                    
                    
                      
makeLongitudeAxis <- function(name, values, bounds = NULL, attributes = NULL) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    76
                    !
                    
                      
  if (!.is_valid_name(name))

                    		
                  

                  

                    77
                    !
                    
                      
    stop("Name for axis is not valid", call. = FALSE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    78
                    
                    
                      
  # FIXME: Check domain

                    		
                  

                  

                    79
                    
                    
                      
  # FIXME: Arguments should not be NULL

                    		
                  

                  

                    80
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    81
                    !
                    
                      
  axis <- CFAxisLongitude$new(name, values = values, attributes = attributes)

                    		
                  

                  

                    82
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    83
                    !
                    
                      
  if (is.na(axis$attribute("standard_name"))) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    84
                    !
                    
                      
    axis$set_attribute("standard_name", "NC_CHAR", "longitude")

                    		
                  

                  

                    85
                    !
                    
                      
    axis$set_attribute("units", "NC_CHAR", "degrees_east")

                    		
                  

                  

                    86
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    87
                    !
                    
                      
  if (!is.null(bounds)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    88
                    !
                    
                      
    nm <- paste0(name, "_bnds")

                    		
                  

                  

                    89
                    !
                    
                      
    axis$bounds <- CFBounds$new(nm, bounds)

                    		
                  

                  

                    90
                    !
                    
                      
    axis$set_attribute("bounds", "NC_CHAR", nm)

                    		
                  

                  

                    91
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    92
                    !
                    
                      
  axis

                    		
                  

                  

                    93
                    
                    
                      
}

makeTimeAxis <- function(name, values, attributes = NULL) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    175
                    !

                    !

                    !

                    !

                    !
