                    229
                    
                    
                      
#' Create a `CFVariable` instance from an R object

                    		
                  

                  

                    230
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    231
                    
                    
                      
#' With this function you can convert an R object into a [CFVariable]. This can

                    		
                  

                  

                    232
                    
                    
                      
#' be an array, matrix or vector of type `logical`, `integer`, `numeric` or

                    		
                  

                  

                    233
                    
                    
                      
#' `character.`

                    		
                  

                  

                    234
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    235
                    
                    
                      
#' Dimnames on the R object will be converted to instances of a [CFAxis]

                    		
                  

                  

                    236
                    
                    
                      
#' descendant class, depending on their values. If the dimnames along a

                    		
                  

                  

                    237
                    
                    
                      
#' dimension of the R object can be converted to `numeric`, then it will be an

                    		
                  

                  

                    238
                    
                    
                      
#' instance of [CFAxisNumeric]. If the dimnames are `character`, a first attempt

                    		
                  

                  

                    239
                    
                    
                      
#' is made to create a [CFAxisTime] (i.e. the dimnames have to represent

                    		
                  

                  

                    240
                    
                    
                      
#' timestamps), failing that a [CFAxisCharacter] will be created. If no dimnames

                    		
                  

                  

                    241
                    
                    
                      
#' are set, an instance of [CFAxisDiscrete] is generated.

                    		
                  

                  

                    242
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    243
                    
                    
                      
#' The axes of the `CFVariable` are oriented as in the R object. Note that this

                    		
                  

                  

                    244
                    
                    
                      
#' is different from standard practice in the netCDF community and the

                    		
                  

                  

                    245
                    
                    
                      
#' portability of saved datasets is thus limited. You can improve this situation

                    		
                  

                  

                    246
                    
                    
                      
#' by setting the orientation of the axes and by adding attributes.

                    		
                  

                  

                    247
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    248
                    
                    
                      
#' After creation of the `CFVariable`, it is recommended to set other

                    		
                  

                  

                    249
                    
                    
                      
#' properties, such as attributes or a coordinate reference system.

                    		
                  

                  

                    250
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    251
                    
                    
                      
#' @param name The name of the `CFVariable` to create.

                    		
                  

                  

                    252
                    
                    
                      
#' @param values The data of this object. This can be an array, matrix or vector

                    		
                  

                  

                    253
                    
                    
                      
#'   of type `logical`, `integer`, `numeric` or `character.`

                    		
                  

                  

                    254
                    
                    
                      
#' @return An instance of class [CFVariable].

                    		
                  

                  

                    255
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    256
                    
                    
                      
as_CF <- function(name, values) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    257
                    
                    
                      
  # Check the properties of "values" and create axes from dimnames

                    		
                  

                  

                    258
                    !
                    
                      
  if (is.logical(values)) values <- as.integer(values)

                    		
                  

                  

                    259
                    2x
                    
                      
  dt <- typeof(values)

                    		
                  

                  

                    260
                    2x
                    
                      
  if (!(dt %in% c("integer", "double", "character")))

                    		
                  

                  

                    261
                    
                    
                      
    stop("Argument 'values' is of an unsupported type", call. = FALSE) # nocov

                    		
                  

                  

                    262
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    263
                    
                    
                      
  # Helper function - "nm" is name for the axis, "len" is length of the dimension, "vals" is coordinate values

                    		
                  

                  

                    264
                    2x
                    
                      
  .makeArrayAxis <- function(nm, len, vals) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    265
                    6x
                    
                      
    if (is.null(vals))              # values has no dimnames so make discrete axis

                    		
                  

                  

                    266
                    3x
                    
                      
      return(CFAxisDiscrete$new(nm, len))

                    		
                  

                  

                    267
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    268
                    3x
                    
                      
    crds <- suppressWarnings(as.numeric(vals))

                    		
                  

                  

                    269
                    3x
                    
                      
    if (any(is.na(crds))) {         # Not numeric so time or character

                    		
                  

                  

                    270
                    1x
                    
                      
      t <- try(CFtime::CFTime$new("days since 1970-01-01T00:00:00", "standard", vals), silent = TRUE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    271
                    1x
                    
                      
      if (inherits(t, "try-error")) # Not time

                    		
                  

                  

                    272
                    !
                    
                      
        CFAxisCharacter$new(nm, values = vals)

                    		
                  

                  

                    273
                    1x
                    
                      
      else CFAxisTime$new(nm, t)

                    		
                  

                  

                    274
                    
                    
                      
    } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    275
                    
                    
                      
      # Check if we have a potential longitude or latitude axis

                    		
                  

                  

                    276
                    2x
                    
                      
      if (tolower(nm) %in% c("longitude", "lon") && .check_longitude_domain(crds))

                    		
                  

                  

                    277
                    !
                    
                      
        CFAxisLongitude$new(nm, values = crds)

                    		
                  

                  

                    278
                    2x
                    
                      
      else if (tolower(nm) %in% c("latitude", "lat") && .check_latitude_domain(vals))

                    		
                  

                  

                    279
                    !
                    
                      
        CFAxisLatitude$new(nm, values = crds)

                    		
                  

                  

                    280
                    
                    
                      
      else

                    		
                  

                  

                    281
                    2x
                    
                      
        CFAxisNumeric$new(nm, values = crds)

                    		
                  

                  

                    282
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    283
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    284
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    285
                    2x
                    
                      
  dims <- dim(values)

                    		
                  

                  

                    286
                    2x
                    
                      
  if (is.null(dims))  # values is a vector

                    		
                  

                  

                    287
                    !
                    
                      
    axes <- list(axis1 = .makeArrayAxis("axis_1", length(values), names(values)))

                    		
                  

                  

                    288
                    
                    
                      
  else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    289
                    2x
                    
                      
    dn <- dimnames(values)

                    		
                  

                  

                    290
                    2x
                    
                      
    names <- names(dn)

                    		
                  

                  

                    291
                    2x
                    
                      
    if (is.null(names))

                    		
                  

                  

                    292
                    1x
                    
                      
      names <- sapply(seq_along(dims), function(x) paste0("axis_", x))

                    		
                  

                  

                    293
                    
                    
                      
    else

                    		
                  

                  

                    294
                    1x
                    
                      
      names <- sapply(seq_along(dims), function(x) if (nzchar(names[x])) names[x] else paste0("axis_", x))

                    		
                  

                  

                    295
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    296
                    2x
                    
                      
    axes <- lapply(seq_along(dims), function(x) .makeArrayAxis(names[x], dims[x], dn[[x]]))

                    		
                  

                  

                    297
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    298
                    2x
                    
                      
  axes <- axes[lengths(axes) > 0L]

                    		
                  

                  

                    299
                    2x
                    
                      
  if (length(axes))

                    2x
                    
                      
    names(axes) <- sapply(axes, function(ax) ax$name)

                    		
                  

                  

                    301
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    302
                    2x

                    303
                    
                    
                      
}

                    		
                  

                
              

            

            

              

                
                  

                    1
                    
                    
                      
#' Area of Interest

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
#' @description This function constructs the area of interest of an analysis. It

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
#'   consists of an extent and a resolution of longitude and latitude, all in

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#'   decimal degrees.

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#'   The AOI is used to define the subset of data to be extracted from a data

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#'   variable that has an auxiliary longitude-latitude grid (see the

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#'   [CFAuxiliaryLongLat] class) at a specified resolution. The data variable

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
#'   thus has a primary coordinate system where the horizontal components are

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#'   not a geographic system of longitude and latitude coordinates.

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
#' @details Following the CF Metadata Conventions, axis coordinates represent

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
#'   the center of grid cells. So when specifying `aoi(20, 30, -10, 10, 1, 2)`,

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
#'   the south-west grid cell coordinate is at `(20.5, -9)`. If the axes of the

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
#'   longitude-latitude grid have bounds, then the bounds will coincide with the

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
#'   AOI and the `CFVariable$subset()` method that uses the AOI will attach

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      
#'   those bounds as attributes to the resulting array.

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      
#'   If no resolution is specified, it will be determined from the separation

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    
                    
                      
#'   between adjacent grid cells in both longitude and latitude directions in

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    
                    
                      
#'   the middle of the area of interest. If no extent is specified (meaning,

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    
                    
                      
#'   none of the values; if some but not all values are specified an error will

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    
                    
                      
#'   be thrown), then the whole extent of the variable is used, extended

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    
                    
                      
#'   outwards by the bounds if they are set or half the resolution otherwise.

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    
                    
                      
#'   Thus, to get the entire extent of the variable but in a longitude-latitude

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    
                    
                      
#'   grid and with a resolution comparable to the resolution at the original

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    
                    
                      
#'   Cartesian coordinate system of the variable, simply pass `aoi()` as an

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    
                    
                      
#'   argument to [CFVariable$subset()][CFVariable]. Note that any missing

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    
                    
                      
#'   arguments are calculated internally and stored in the returned object, but

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    
                    
                      
#'   only after the call to `CFVariable$subset()`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    
                    
                      
#'   ## Caching

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    
                    
                      
#'   In data collections that are composed of multiple data variables in a

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    
                    
                      
#'   single netCDF resource, a single auxiliary longitude-latitude grid may be

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    
                    
                      
#'   referenced by multiple data variables, such as in

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    
                    
                      
#'   [ROMS](https://www.myroms.org) data which may have dozens of data variables

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    
                    
                      
#'   using a shared grid. When subsetting with an AOI, the instance of this

                    		
                  

                  

                    40
                    
                    
                      
#'   class is cached to improve performance. The successive calls to

                    		
                  

                  

                    41
                    
                    
                      
#'   `CFVariable$subset()` should use the same object returned from a single

                    		
                  

                  

                    42
                    
                    
                      
#'   call to this function for this caching to work properly.

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    44
                    
                    
                      
#' @param lonMin,lonMax,latMin,latMax The minimum and maximum values of the

                    		
                  

                  

                    45
                    
                    
                      
#'   longitude and latitude of the AOI, in decimal degrees. The longitude values

                    		
                  

                  

                    46
                    
                    
                      
#'   must agree with the range of the longitude in the data variable to which

                    		
                  

                  

                    47
                    
                    
                      
#'   this AOI will be applied, e.g. `[-180,180]` or `[0,360]`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    48
                    
                    
                      
#' @param resX,resY The separation between adjacent grid cell, in the longitude

                    		
                  

                  

                    49
                    
                    
                      
#'   and latitude directions respectively, in decimal degrees. The permitted

                    		
                  

                  

                    50
                    
                    
                      
#'   values lie within the range `[0.01 ... 10]`. If `resY` is missing it will

                    		
                  

                  

                    51
                    
                    
                      
#'   use the value of `resX`, yielding square grid cells.

                    		
                  

                  

                    52
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    53
                    
                    
                      
#' @return The return value of the function is an `R6` object which uses

                    		
                  

                  

                    54
                    
                    
                      
#'   reference semantics. Making changes to the returned object will be visible

                    		
                  

                  

                    55
                    
                    
                      
#'   in all copies made of the object.

                    		
                  

                  

                    56
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    57
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    58
                    
                    
                      
#' @examples

                    		
                  

                  

                    59
                    
                    
                      
#' (aoi <- aoi(20, 60, -40, -20, 0.5))

                    		
                  

                  

                    60
                    
                    
                      
aoi <- function(lonMin, lonMax, latMin, latMax, resX, resY) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    61
                    2x
                    
                      
  if (missing(resX)) resolution <- NULL

                    		
                  

                  

                    62
                    
                    
                      
  else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    63
                    2x
                    
                      
    if (missing(resY)) resY <- resX

                    		
                  

                  

                    64
                    2x
                    
                      
    resolution <- c(resX, resY)

                    		
                  

                  

                    65
                    2x
                    
                      
    .aoi_check_resolution(resolution)

                    		
                  

                  

                    66
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    67
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    68
                    4x
                    
                      
  if (missing(lonMin) && missing(lonMin) && missing(lonMin) && missing(lonMin))

                    		
                  

                  

                    69
                    !
                    
                      
    AOI$new(NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, resolution)

                    		
                  

                  

                    70
                    
                    
                      
  else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    71
                    4x
                    
                      
    .aoi_check_longitude(lonMin, lonMax)

                    		
                  

                  

                    72
                    4x
                    
                      
    .aoi_check_latitude(latMin, latMax)

                    		
                  

                  

                    73
                    4x
                    
                      
    AOI$new(lonMin, lonMax, latMin, latMax, resolution)

                    		
                  

                  

                    74
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    75
                    
                    
                      
}

    check_start_count = function(start, count) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    63
                    253x

                    64
                    253x

                    65
                    9x

                    66
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    67
                    244x

open_ncdf <- function(resource) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      
  # Parameter check

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    24x
                    
                      
  if (length(resource) != 1L && !is.character(resource))

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    
                    
                      
    stop("Argument `resource` must be a single character string pointing to a netCDF resource.", call. = FALSE) # nocov

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    24x

                    25
                    24x

                    26
                    24x

                    27

                    24x

                    30

                    31
                    24x

                    33

                    34
                    24x
                    
                      
  axes <- .buildAxes(root)

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    
                    
                      
  # Find the id's of any "bounds" variables

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    24x
                    
                      
  bnds <- sapply(root$NCvars, function(v) { # FIXME: what about dims in subgroups?

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    168x
                    
                      
    nm <- v$attribute("bounds")

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    
                    
                      
    # FIXME: climatology

                    		
                  

                  

                    40
                    168x
                    
                      
    if (!is.na(nm)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    41
                    32x
                    
                      
      obj <- v$group$find_by_name(nm, "NC")

                    		
                  

                  

                    42
                    32x
                    
                      
      if (is.null(obj)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    !
                    
                      
        warning("Unmatched `bounds` value '", nm, "' found in variable '", v$name, "'.", call. = FALSE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    44
                    !
                    
                      
        -1L

                    		
                  

                  

                    45
                    32x
                    
                      
      } else obj$dimids[1L]    # By definition, bounds dimid comes first

                    		
                  

                  

                    46
                    136x
                    
                      
    } else -1L # Flag no bounds

                    		
                  

                  

                    47
                    
                    
                      
  })

                    		
                  

                  

                    48
                    24x
                    
                      
  if (length(bnds))

                    		
                  

                  

                    49
                    23x
                    
                      
    bnds <- unique(bnds[which(bnds > -1L)])

                    		
                  

                  

                    50
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    51
                    
                    
                      
  # Mop up any non-CV dimensions except bounds - additional to CF Conventions

                    		
                  

                  

                    52
                    24x
                    
                      
  all_axis_dims <- sapply(axes, function(x) x$dimid)

                    		
                  

                  

                    53
                    24x
                    
                      
  all_axis_dims <- all_axis_dims[!is.na(all_axis_dims)]

                    		
                  

                  

                    54
                    24x
                    
                      
  all_var_dims <- unique(unlist(sapply(root$NCvars, function(v) v$dimids)))

                    		
                  

                  

                    55
                    24x
                    
                      
  all_var_dims <- all_var_dims[!is.na(all_var_dims)]

                    		
                  

                  

                    56
                    24x
                    
                      
  add_dims <- all_var_dims[!(all_var_dims %in% c(all_axis_dims, bnds))]

                    		
                  

                  

                    57
                    24x
                    
                      
  if (length(add_dims)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    58
                    1x
                    
                      
    axes <- append(axes, .addBareDimensions(root, add_dims))

                    		
                  

                  

                    59
                    1x
                    
                      
    axes <- axes[lengths(axes) > 0L]

                    		
                  

                  

                    60
                    
                    
                      
    #names(root$CFaxes) <- sapply(root$CFaxes, function(x) x$name)

                    		
                  

                  

                    61
                    
                    
                      
    #names(root$NCvars) <- sapply(root$NCvars, function(v) v$name)

                    63

  # Auxiliary CVs and scalar CVs

                    		
                  

                  

                    65
                    24x

                    66
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    67
                    
                    
                      
  # Cell measure variables

                    		
                  

                  

                    68
                    24x

                    69
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    70
                    
                    
                      
  # Coordinate reference systems

                    		
                  

                  

                    71
                    24x
                    
                      
  .makeCRS(root)

                    		
                  

                  

                    72
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    73
                    24x
                    
                      
  if (length(axes)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    74
                    
                    
                      
    # Try to identify the type of the file

                    		
                  

                  

                    75
                    23x
                    
                      
    ds$file_type <- if (!is.na(ft <- root$attribute("featureType")) &&

                    		
                  

                  

                    76
                    23x
                    
                      
        ft %in% c("point", "timeSeries", "trajectory", "profile", "timeSeriesProfile", "trajectoryProfile"))

                    		
                  

                  

                    77
                    23x
                    
                      
      "discrete sampling geometry"

                    		
                  

                  

                    78
                    23x
                    
                      
    else if (!is.na(mip_era <- root$attribute("mip_era")))

                    		
                  

                  

                    79
                    23x
                    
                      
      mip_era

                    		
                  

                  

                    80
                    23x
                    
                      
    else if (!is.na(crd <- root$attribute("project_id")) && crd == "CORDEX")

                    		
                  

                  

                    81
                    23x
                    
                      
      "CORDEX"

                    		
                  

                  

                    82
                    23x
                    
                      
    else "Generic netCDF data"

                    		
                  

                  

                    83
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    84
                    
                    
                      
    # Configure any parametric vertical axes

                    		
                  

                  

                    85
                    23x
                    
                      
    lapply(root$CFaxes, function(ax) ax$configure_terms(root$CFaxes))

                    		
                  

                  

                    86
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    87
                    23x
                    
                      
    vars <- .buildVariables(root, root$CFaxes)

                    		
                  

                  

                    88
                    
                    
                      
  } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    89
                    
                    
                      
    # Try L3b

                    		
                  

                  

                    90
                    1x
                    
                      
    units <- root$attribute("units")

                    		
                  

                  

                    91
                    1x
                    
                      
    if (!is.na(units)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    92
                    1x
                    
                      
      units <- strsplit(units, ":")[[1L]]

                    		
                  

                  

                    93
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    94
                    1x
                    
                      
      l3bgrp <- root$subgroups[["level-3_binned_data"]]

                    		
                  

                  

                    95
                    1x
                    
                      
      if (!is.null(l3bgrp)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    96
                    1x
                    
                      
        nm <- names(l3bgrp$NCvars)

                    		
                  

                  

                    97
                    1x
                    
                      
        if (all(c("BinList", "BinIndex", units[1L]) %in% nm)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    98
                    1x
                    
                      
          ds$file_type <- "NASA level-3 binned data"

                    		
                  

                  

                    99
                    1x
                    
                      
          l3bgrp$CFvars <- setNames(list(CFVariableL3b$new(l3bgrp, units)), units[1L])

                    		
                  

                  

                    100
                    
                    
                      
        }

                    		
                  

                  

                    101
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    102
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    103
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    104
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    105
                    24x
                    
                      
  ds$root <- root

                    		
                  

                  

                    106
                    24x
                    
                      
  ds

                    		
                  

                  

                    107
                    
                    
                      
}

#' Examine a netCDF resource

                    		
                  

                  

                    110
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    111
                    
                    
                      
#' This function will read a netCDF resource and return a list of identifying

                    		
                  

                  

                    112
                    
                    
                      
#' information, including data variables, axes and global attributes. Upon

                    		
                  

                  

                    113
                    
                    
                      
#' returning the netCDF resource is closed.

                    		
                  

                  

                    114
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    115
                    
                    
                      
#' If you find that you need other information to be included in the result,

                    		
                  

                  

                    116
                    
                    
                      
#' [open an issue](https://github.com/R-CF/ncdfCF/issues).

                    		
                  

                  

                    117
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    118
                    
                    
                      
#' @param resource The name of the netCDF resource to open, either a local file

                    		
                  

                  

                    119
                    
                    
                      
#'   name or a remote URI.

                    		
                  

                  

                    120
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    121
                    
                    
                      
#' @return A list with elements "variables", "axes" and global "attributes",

                    		
                  

                  

                    122
                    
                    
                      
#' each a `data.frame`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    123
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    124
                    
                    
                      
#' @examples

                    		
                  

                  

                    125
                    
                    
                      
#' fn <- system.file("extdata",

                    		
                  

                  

                    126
                    
                    
                      
#'   "pr_day_EC-Earth3-CC_ssp245_r1i1p1f1_gr_20230101-20231231_vncdfCF.nc",

                    		
                  

                  

                    127
                    
                    
                      
#'   package = "ncdfCF")

                    		
                  

                  

                    128
                    
                    
                      
#' peek_ncdf(fn)

                    		
                  

                  

                    129
                    
                    
                      
peek_ncdf <- function(resource) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    130
                    1x
                    
                      
  ds <- open_ncdf(resource)

                    		
                  

                  

                    131
                    1x
                    
                      
  grps <- ds$has_subgroups()

                    		
                  

                  

                    132
                    1x
                    
                      
  if (inherits(ds, "CFDataset")) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    133
                    1x
                    
                      
    list(uri = ds$uri,

                    		
                  

                  

                    134
                    1x
                    
                      
         type = ds$file_type,

                    		
                  

                  

                    135
                    1x
                    
                      
         variables  = do.call(rbind, lapply(ds$variables(), function(v) v$peek())),

                    		
                  

                  

                    136
                    1x
                    
                      
         axes       = do.call(rbind, lapply(ds$axes(), function(a) a$peek())),

                    		
                  

                  

                    137
                    1x
                    
                      
         attributes = ds$attributes())

                    		
                  

                  

                    138
                    
                    
                      
  } else list() # nocov

                    		
                  

                  

                    139
                    
                    
                      
}

#' Read a group from a netCDF dataset

                    		
                  

                  

                    142
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    143
                    
                    
                      
#' Variable, dimension, UDT and attribute information are read for the group, as

                    		
                  

                  

                    144
                    
                    
                      
#' well as all subgroups.

                    		
                  

                  

                    145
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    146
                    
                    
                      
#' @param parent The parent `NCGroup` of this group. `NULL` for the root group.

                    		
                  

                  

                    147
                    
                    
                      
#' @param h The handle to the group in the netCDF resource.

                    		
                  

                  

                    148
                    
                    
                      
#' @param parent_dims The dimids that have been seen at higher levels.

                    		
                  

                  

                    149
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    150
                    
                    
                      
#' @return Either the `NCGroup` instance invisibly or a try-error instance.

                    		
                  

                  

                    151
                    
                    
                      
#' @noRd

.readGroup <- function(parent, h, parent_dims) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    153
                    27x
                    
                      
  g <- RNetCDF::grp.inq.nc(h)

                    		
                  

                  

                    154
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    155
                    
                    
                      
  # Global attributes

                    		
                  

                  

                    156
                    27x
                    
                      
  atts <- if (g$ngatts) .readAttributes(h, "NC_GLOBAL", g$ngatts)

                    		
                  

                  

                    157
                    27x
                    
                      
          else data.frame()

                    		
                  

                  

                    158
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    159
                    27x
                    
                      
  grp <- NCGroup$new(id = as.integer(g$self), name = g$name, atts,

                    		
                  

                  

                    160
                    27x
                    
                      
                     parent = parent, resource = parent$resource)

                    		
                  

                  

                    161
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    162
                    
                    
                      
  # Read all the raw NC variables in the group

                    		
                  

                  

                    163
                    27x
                    
                      
  if (length(g$varids))

                    		
                  

                  

                    164
                    24x
                    
                      
    lapply(g$varids, function (v) .readNCVariable(grp, g$self, v))

                    		
                  

                  

                    165
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    166
                    
                    
                      
  # Dimensions by dimid

                    		
                  

                  

                    167
                    27x
                    
                      
  if (length(g$dimids) && length(new_dims <- g$dimids[!(g$dimids %in% parent_dims)]))

                    		
                  

                  

                    168
                    24x
                    
                      
    dims <- lapply(new_dims, function (d) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    169
                    93x
                    
                      
      dmeta <- RNetCDF::dim.inq.nc(h, d)

                    		
                  

                  

                    170
                    93x
                    
                      
      NCDimension$new(dmeta$id, dmeta$name, dmeta$length, dmeta$unlim, grp)

                    		
                  

                  

                    171
                    
                    
                      
    })

                    		
                  

                  

                    172
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    173
                    
                    
                      
  # UDTs

                    		
                  

                  

                    174
                    27x
                    
                      
  if (length(g$typeids))

                    		
                  

                  

                    175
                    1x
                    
                      
    grp$NCudts <- lapply(g$typeids, function(t) RNetCDF::type.inq.nc(h, t, fields = TRUE))

                    		
                  

                  

                    176
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    177
                    
                    
                      
  # Subgroups

                    		
                  

                  

                    178
                    27x
                    
                      
  if (length(g$grps)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    179
                    2x
                    
                      
    grp$subgroups <- lapply(g$grps, function(z) .readGroup(grp, z, g$dimids))

                    		
                  

                  

                    180
                    2x
                    
                      
    names(grp$subgroups) <- sapply(grp$subgroups, function(z) z$name)

                    		
                  

                  

                    181
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    182
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    183
                    27x
                    
                      
  grp

                    		
                  

                  

                    184
                    
                    
                      
}

#' Read a raw NC variable from a group, everything except its data

.readNCVariable <- function(grp, h, vid) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    189
                    171x

                    171x

                    191
                    171x
                    
                      
                 vtype = vmeta$type, dimids = vmeta$dimids,

                    		
                  

                  

                    192
                    171x
                    
                      
                 attributes = .readAttributes(h, vmeta$name, vmeta$natts),

                    		
                  

                  

                    193

}

.buildAxes <- function(grp) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    197
                    27x
                    
                      
  if (length(grp$NCvars) > 0L) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    198

                    24x

                    !

}

# Create an `CFAxis` from an NC variable and dimension

                    		
                  

                  

                    218
                    
                    
                      
#

                    		
                  

                  

                    219
                    
                    
                      
# This method creates the various kinds of axes.

                    		
                  

                  

                    220
                    
                    
                      
#

                    		
                  

                  

                    221

                    222
                    
                    
                      
# @param var `NCVariable` instance to create the axis from.

                    		
                  

                  

                    223
                    
                    
                      
#

                    		
                  

                  

                    224
                    
                    
                      
# @return An instance of `CFAxis`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    225

.makeAxis <- function(grp, var) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    227
                    78x
                    
                      
  h <- grp$handle

                    		
                  

                  

                    228
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    229
                    
                    
                      
  # Dimension values

                    		
                  

                  

                    230
                    78x
                    
                      
  vals <- try(as.vector(RNetCDF::var.get.nc(h, var$name)), silent = TRUE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    231
                    78x
                    
                      
  if (inherits(vals, "try-error"))

                    		
                  

                  

                    232
                    
                    
                      
    # No dimension values so it's an identity axis

                    		
                  

                  

                    233
                    !
                    
                      
    return(CFAxisDiscrete$new(var))

                    		
                  

                  

                    234
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    235
                    
                    
                      
  # Does `var` have attributes?

                    		
                  

                  

                    236
                    78x
                    
                      
  if (!nrow(var$attributes)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    237
                    
                    
                      
    # No attributes so nothing left to do

                    		
                  

                  

                    238
                    !
                    
                      
    if (var$vtype %in% c("NC_CHAR", "NC_STRING"))

                    		
                  

                  

                    239
                    !
                    
                      
      return(CFAxisCharacter$new(var, values = vals))

                    		
                  

                  

                    240
                    !
                    
                      
    else return(CFAxisNumeric$new(var, values = vals))

                    		
                  

                  

                    241
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    242
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    243
                    
                    
                      
  # Read some useful attributes

                    		
                  

                  

                    244
                    78x
                    
                      
  orient   <- var$attribute("axis")

                    		
                  

                  

                    245
                    78x
                    
                      
  standard <- var$attribute("standard_name")

                    		
                  

                  

                    246
                    78x
                    
                      
  units    <- var$attribute("units")

                    		
                  

                  

                    247
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    248
                    
                    
                      
  # Read the boundary values

                    		
                  

                  

                    249
                    78x
                    
                      
  bnds <- .readBounds(grp, var$attribute("bounds"))

                    		
                  

                  

                    250
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    251
                    
                    
                      
  # See if we can make time

                    		
                  

                  

                    252
                    78x
                    
                      
  t <- .makeTimeObject(var, units, vals, bnds)

                    		
                  

                  

                    253
                    78x
                    
                      
  if (!is.null(t)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    254
                    22x
                    
                      
    tax <- CFAxisTime$new(var, t)

                    		
                  

                  

                    255
                    22x
                    
                      
    tax$bounds <- bnds

                    		
                  

                  

                    256
                    22x
                    
                      
    return(tax)

                    		
                  

                  

                    257
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    258
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    259
                    
                    
                      
  # Create the axis based on units

                    		
                  

                  

                    260
                    56x
                    
                      
  axis <- if (!is.na(units)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    261
                    52x
                    
                      
    if (grepl("^degree(s?)(_?)(east|E)$", units))

                    17x

                    35x

                    264
                    17x

                    265
                    18x

      CFAxisVertical$new(var, values = vals)

                    		
                  

                  

                    267
                    
                    
                      
    else

                    		
                  

                  

                    268
                    18x
                    
                      
      NULL

                    		
                  

                  

                    269
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    270
                    56x
                    
                      
  if (is.null(axis) && !is.na(standard)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    271
                    14x
                    
                      
    axis <- switch(standard,

                    		
                  

                  

                    272
                    14x
                    
                      
                   "longitude" = CFAxisLongitude$new(var, values = vals),

                    		
                  

                  

                    273
                    14x
                    
                      
                   "latitude"  = CFAxisLatitude$new(var, values = vals),

.addBareDimensions <- function(grp, add_dims) {

                    !

.makeTimeObject <- function(var, units, vals, bnds) {

#' Make CF constructs for "coordinates" references

                    		
                  

                  

                    342
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    343
                    
                    
                      
#' NC variables are scanned for a "coordinates" attribute (which must be a data

                    		
                  

                  

                    344
                    
                    
                      
#' variable, domain variable or geometry container variable). If not already

                    		
                  

                  

                    345
                    
                    
                      
#' present, the NC variable referenced is converted into one of 3 objects,

                    		
                  

                  

                    346
                    
                    
                      
#' depending on context: 1. A scalar coordinate variable in the group where its

                    		
                  

                  

                    347
                    
                    
                      
#' NC variable is located; 2. A label variable in the group where its NC

                    		
                  

                  

                    348
                    
                    
                      
#' variable is located; multiple label coordinates (such as in the case of taxon

                    		
                  

                  

                    349
                    
                    
                      
#' name and identifier) are stored in a single label variable; 3. A long-lat

                    		
                  

                  

                    350
                    
                    
                      
#' auxiliary coordinate variable when both a longitude and latitude NC variable

                    		
                  

                  

                    351
                    
                    
                      
#' are found, in the group of the longitude NC variable.

                    		
                  

                  

                    352
                    
                    
                      
#' @param grp The group to scan.

                    		
                  

                  

                    353
                    
                    
                      
#' @return Nothing. CFAxis and CFAuxiliaryLongLat instances are created in the

                    		
                  

                  

                    354
                    
                    
                      
#'   groups where the NC variables are found. These will later be picked up when

                    		
                  

                  

                    355
                    
                    
                      
#'   CFvariables are created.

                    		
                  

                  

                    356
                    
                    
                      
#' @noRd

                    		
                  

                  

                    357
                    
                    
                      
.makeCoordinates <- function(grp) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    358
                    27x
                    
                      
  if (length(grp$NCvars) > 0L) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    359
                    
                    
                      
    # Scan each unused NCVariable for the "coordinates" attribute and process.

                    		
                  

                  

                    360
                    
                    
                      
    # The NCVariable must have dimensional axes.

                    		
                  

                  

                    361
                    24x
                    
                      
    for (refid in seq_along(grp$NCvars)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    362
                    171x
                    
                      
      v <- grp$NCvars[[refid]]

                    		
                  

                  

                    363
                    171x
                    
                      
      if (!length(v$CF) && length(vdimids <- v$dimids) &&

                    		
                  

                  

                    364
                    171x
                    
                      
          !is.na(coords <- v$attribute("coordinates"))) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    365
                    9x
                    
                      
        coords <- strsplit(coords, " ", fixed = TRUE)[[1L]]

                    		
                  

                  

                    366
                    9x
                    
                      
        varLon <- varLat <- bndsLon <- bndsLat <- NA

                    		
                  

                  

                    367
                    9x
                    
                      
        for (cid in seq_along(coords)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    368
                    30x
                    
                      
          found_one <- FALSE
