                    30x
                    
                      
          aux <- grp$find_by_name(coords[cid], "NC")

                    		
                  

                  

                    370
                    30x
                    
                      
          if (!is.null(aux)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    371
                    26x
                    
                      
            nd <- aux$ndims

                    		
                  

                  

                    372
                    26x
                    
                      
            bounds <- aux$attribute("bounds")

                    		
                  

                  

                    373
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    374
                    
                    
                      
            # If aux is a 2D NCVariable having an attribute "units" with value

                    		
                  

                  

                    375
                    
                    
                      
            # "degrees_east" or "degrees_north" it is a longitude or latitude,

                    		
                  

                  

                    376
                    
                    
                      
            # respectively. Record the fact and move on.

                    		
                  

                  

                    377
                    26x
                    
                      
            if (nd == 2L && !is.na(units <- aux$attribute("units"))) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    378
                    12x
                    
                      
              if (grepl("^degree(s?)(_?)(east|E)$", units)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    379
                    6x
                    
                      
                varLon <- aux

                    		
                  

                  

                    380
                    6x
                    
                      
                bndsLon <- .readBounds(aux$group, bounds)

                    		
                  

                  

                    381
                    6x
                    
                      
                found_one <- TRUE

                    		
                  

                  

                    382
                    6x
                    
                      
              } else if (grepl("^degree(s?)(_?)(north|N)$", units)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    383
                    6x
                    
                      
                varLat <- aux

                    		
                  

                  

                    384
                    6x
                    
                      
                bndsLat <- .readBounds(aux$group, bounds)

                    		
                  

                  

                    385
                    6x
                    
                      
                found_one <- TRUE

                    		
                  

                  

                    386
                    
                    
                      
              }

                    		
                  

                  

                    387
                    
                    
                      
            }

                    		
                  

                  

                    388
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    389
                    26x
                    
                      
            if (!found_one) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    390
                    14x
                    
                      
              if (nd > 0L && aux$vtype %in% c("NC_CHAR", "NC_STRING")) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    391
                    
                    
                      
                # Label

                    		
                  

                  

                    392
                    4x
                    
                      
                aux$group$CFaux[[aux$name]] <- CFLabel$new(aux)

                    		
                  

                  

                    393
                    4x
                    
                      
                found_one <- TRUE

                    		
                  

                  

                    394
                    10x
                    
                      
              } else if (nd < 2L) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    395
                    
                    
                      
                # Scalar or auxiliary coordinate with a single dimension: make an axis out of it if it doesn't already exist.

                    		
                  

                  

                    396
                    10x
                    
                      
                if (is.null(grp$find_by_name(aux$name))) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    397
                    4x
                    
                      
                  new_ax <- list(.makeAxis(grp, aux))

                    		
                  

                  

                    398
                    4x
                    
                      
                  names(new_ax) <- aux$name

                    		
                  

                  

                    399
                    4x
                    
                      
                  aux$group$CFaux <- append(aux$group$CFaux, new_ax)

                    		
                  

                  

                    400
                    
                    
                      
                }

                    		
                  

                  

                    401
                    10x
                    
                      
                found_one <- TRUE

                    		
                  

                  

                    402
                    
                    
                      
              }

                    		
                  

                  

                    403
                    
                    
                      
            }

                    		
                  

                  

                    404
                    
                    
                      
          }

                    		
                  

                  

                    405
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    406
                    30x
                    
                      
          if (!found_one)

                    		
                  

                  

                    407
                    4x
                    
                      
            warning("Unmatched `coordinates` value '", coords[cid], "' found in variable '", v$name, "'.", call. = FALSE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    408
                    
                    
                      
        }

                    		
                  

                  

                    409
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    410
                    
                    
                      
        # Make a CFAuxiliaryLongLat if we have found a varLon and a varLat and

                    		
                  

                  

                    411
                    
                    
                      
        # they have identical dimensions, in the varLon group.

                    		
                  

                  

                    412
                    9x
                    
                      
        if ((inherits(varLon, "NCVariable") && inherits(varLat, "NCVariable")) &&

                    		
                  

                  

                    413
                    9x
                    
                      
            identical(varLon$dimids, varLat$dimids)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    414
                    6x
                    
                      
          ax <- lapply(varLon$dimids, function(did) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    415
                    12x
                    
                      
            dname <- varLon$group$find_dim_by_id(did)$name

                    		
                  

                  

                    416
                    12x
                    
                      
            varLon$group$find_by_name(dname, "NC")$CF[[1L]]

                    		
                  

                  

                    417
                    
                    
                      
          })

                    		
                  

                  

                    418
                    6x
                    
                      
          lonCF <- CFVariable$new(varLon, ax)

                    		
                  

                  

                    419
                    6x
                    
                      
          latCF <- CFVariable$new(varLat, ax)

                    		
                  

                  

                    420
                    6x
                    
                      
          varLon$group$addAuxiliaryLongLat(lonCF, latCF, bndsLon, bndsLat)

                    		
                  

                  

                    421
                    
                    
                      
        }

                    		
                  

                  

                    422
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    423
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    424
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    425
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    426
                    
                    
                      
  # Descend into subgroups

                    		
                  

                  

                    427
                    27x
                    
                      
  if (length(grp$subgroups))

                    		
                  

                  

                    428
                    2x
                    
                      
    lapply(grp$subgroups, function(g) .makeCoordinates(g))

                    		
                  

                  

                    429
                    
                    
                      
}

.readBounds <- function(grp, bounds) {

#'   The class provides access to the data arrays for longitude and latitude

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#'   from the netCDF resource, as well as all the details that have been

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#'   associated with both axes. Additionally, this class can generate the index

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
#'   to extract values on a long-lat grid of the associated X-Y grid data

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#'   variable using a user-selectable extent and resolution.

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
#'   Auxiliary longitude-latitude grids are only supported for reading from a

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
#'   netCDF resource. Creating an instance of this class manually therefore has

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
#'   no practical purpose.

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
#' @docType class

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      
CFAuxiliaryLongLat <- R6::R6Class("CFAuxiliaryLongLat",

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    
                    
                      
  private = list(

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      
    .ext   = NULL, # The extent of the longitude and latitude grids, in lon min, max, lat min, max

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    
                    
                      
    .res   = c(NULL, NULL), # Resolution of the lat/long grid, vector of (lon, lat)

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    
                    
                      
    .aoi   = NULL, # The AOI for the grid

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    
                    
                      
    .index = NULL, # The index values into the linearized grids that cover the AOI

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    
                    
                      
    # The [CFVariable] instance of the longitude values.

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    
                    
                      
    .varLong = NULL,

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    
                    
                      
    # The [CFVariable] instance of the latitude values.

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    
                    
                      
    .varLat = NULL,

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    
                    
                      
    # The [CFBounds] instance for the longitude values of the grid.

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    
                    
                      
    .boundsLong = NULL,

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    
                    
                      
    # The [CFBounds] instance for the latitude values of the grid.

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    
                    
                      
    .boundsLat = NULL,

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    
                    
                      
    # Either `c("X", "Y")` (default) or `c("Y", "X")` to

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    
                    
                      
    # indicate the orientation of the latitude and longitude grids.

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    
                    
                      
    .axis_order = c("X", "Y"),

                    		
                  

                  

                    40
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    41
                    
                    
                      
    # Set the nominal resolution of the grid at the location indicated. If no

                    		
                  

                  

                    42
                    
                    
                      
    # location is indicated, use the center of the grids. The location must be

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    
                    
                      
    # given as an integer vector of length with indices into the lat-long grids.

    set_resolution = function(location = NULL) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    45
                    8x
                    
                      
      dim <- private$.varLong$dim()

                    		
                  

                  

                    46
                    8x
                    
                      
      if (is.null(location))

                    		
                  

                  

                    47
                    6x
                    
                      
        location <- as.integer(dim * 0.5)

                    		
                  

                  

                    48
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    49
                    8x
                    
                      
      lon <- private$.varLong$read_data()

                    		
                  

                  

                    50
                    8x
                    
                      
      lat <- private$.varLat$read_data()

                    		
                  

                  

                    51
                    8x
                    
                      
      private$.res[1L] <- abs(if (location[1L] == 1L)

                    		
                  

                  

                    52
                    8x
                    
                      
        lon[location[1L] + 1L, location[2L]] - lon[location[1L], location[2L]]

                    		
                  

                  

                    53
                    8x
                    
                      
      else if (location[1L] == dim[1L])

                    		
                  

                  

                    54
                    8x
                    
                      
        lon[location[1L], location[2L]] - lon[location[1L] - 1L, location[2L]]

                    		
                  

                  

                    55
                    
                    
                      
      else

                    		
                  

                  

                    56
                    8x
                    
                      
        (lon[location[1L] + 1L, location[2L]] - lon[location[1L] - 1L, location[2L]]) * 0.5)

                    		
                  

                  

                    57
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    58
                    8x
                    
                      
      private$.res[2L] <- abs(if (location[2L] == 1L)

                    		
                  

                  

                    59
                    8x
                    
                      
        lat[location[1L], location[2L] + 1L] - lat[location[1L], location[2L]]

                    		
                  

                  

                    60
                    8x
                    
                      
      else if (location[2L] == dim[2L])

                    		
                  

                  

                    61
                    8x
                    
                      
        lat[location[1L], location[2L]] - lat[location[1L], location[2L] - 1L]

                    		
                  

                  

                    62
                    
                    
                      
      else

                    		
                  

                  

                    63
                    8x
                    
                      
        (lat[location[1L], location[2L] + 1L] - lat[location[1L], location[2L] - 1L]) * 0.5)

                    		
                  

                  

                    64
                    
                    
                      
    },

                    		
                  

                  

                    65
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    66
                    
                    
                      
    setAOI = function(aoi) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    67
                    2x
                    
                      
      self$clear_cache()

                    		
                  

                  

                    68
                    2x
                    
                      
      private$.aoi <- aoi

                    		
                  

                  

                    69
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    70
                    
                    
                      
      # If there are any NULL values in aoi, use the bounds or extent

                    		
                  

                  

                    71
                    2x
                    
                      
      expand <- FALSE

                    		
                  

                  

                    72
                    2x
                    
                      
      if (is.null(aoi$latMin))

                    		
                  

                  

                    73
                    !
                    
                      
        if (inherits(self$.boundsLong, "CFBounds")) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    74
                    !
                    
                      
          aoi$extent <- c(self$.boundsLong$range(), self$.boundsLat$range())

                    		
                  

                  

                    75
                    
                    
                      
        } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    76
                    !
                    
                      
          aoi$extent <- self$extent

                    		
                  

                  

                    77
                    !
                    
                      
          expand <- TRUE

                    		
                  

                  

                    78
                    
                    
                      
        }

                    		
                  

                  

                    79
                    2x
                    
                      
      lonExt <- aoi$lonMax - aoi$lonMin

                    		
                  

                  

                    80
                    2x
                    
                      
      latExt <- aoi$latMax - aoi$latMin

                    		
                  

                  

                    81
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    82
                    
                    
                      
      # Resolution, use supplied or calculate from grid

                    		
                  

                  

                    83
                    2x
                    
                      
      if (is.null(aoi$resolution)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    84
                    2x
                    
                      
        center <- self$sample_index(aoi$lonMin + lonExt * 0.5, aoi$latMin + latExt * 0.5)[1L,]

                    		
                  

                  

                    85
                    2x
                    
                      
        if (is.na(center[1L]))

                    		
                  

                  

                    86
                    !
                    
                      
          stop("Center of AOI contains no data so resolution cannot be derived. Please specify explicitly.", call. = FALSE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    87
                    2x
                    
                      
        private$set_resolution(center)

                    		
                  

                  

                    88
                    2x
                    
                      
        aoi$resolution <- round(c(private$.res[1L], private$.res[2L]), CF.options$digits)

                    		
                  

                  

                    89
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    90
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    91
                    2x
                    
                      
      if (expand) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    92
                    !
                    
                      
        halfres <- aoi$resolution * 0.5

                    		
                  

                  

                    93
                    !
                    
                      
        aoi$extent <- aoi$extent + c(-halfres[1L], halfres[1L], -halfres[2L], halfres[2L])

                    		
                  

                  

                    94
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    95
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    96
                    
                    
                      
      # Update upper-left to match resolution

                    		
                  

                  

                    97
                    2x
                    
                      
      aoi$lonMax <- if (self$extent[1L] < 0)

                    		
                  

                  

                    98
                    2x
                    
                      
                      min(aoi$lonMin + private$.res[1L] * ceiling(lonExt / private$.res[1L]), 180)

                    		
                  

                  

                    99
                    
                    
                      
                    else

                    		
                  

                  

                    100
                    2x
                    
                      
                      min(aoi$lonMin + private$.res[1L] * ceiling(lonExt / private$.res[1L]), 360)

                    		
                  

                  

                    101
                    2x
                    
                      
      aoi$latMax <- min(aoi$latMin + private$.res[2L] * ceiling(latExt / private$.res[2L]), 90)

                    		
                  

                  

                    102
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    103
                    2x
                    
                      
      invisible(self)

                    		
                  

                  

                    104
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    105
                    
                    
                      
  ),

                    		
                  

                  

                    106
                    
                    
                      
  public = list(

                    		
                  

                  

                    107
                    
                    
                      
    #' @description Creating a new instance. It should normally not be useful to

                    		
                  

                  

                    108
                    
                    
                      
    #'   create an instance of this class other than upon reading a netCDF

                    		
                  

                  

                    109
                    
                    
                      
    #'   resource.

                    		
                  

                  

                    110
                    
                    
                      
    #' @param varLong,varLat The [CFVariable] instances with the longitude and

                    		
                  

                  

                    111
                    
                    
                      
    #'   latitude grid values, respectively.

                    		
                  

                  

                    112
                    
                    
                      
    #' @param boundsLong,boundsLat The [CFBounds] instances of the grid cells

                    		
                  

                  

                    113
                    
                    
                      
    #'   for the longitude and latitude, respectively, if set. Defaults to

                    		
                  

                  

                    114
                    
                    
                      
    #'   `NULL`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    115
                    
                    
                      
    initialize = function(varLong, varLat, boundsLong = NULL, boundsLat = NULL) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    116
                    6x
                    
                      
      private$.varLong <- varLong

                    		
                  

                  

                    117
                    6x
                    
                      
      private$.varLat <- varLat

                    		
                  

                  

                    118
                    6x
                    
                      
      private$.boundsLong <- boundsLong

                    		
                  

                  

                    119
                    6x
                    
                      
      private$.boundsLat <- boundsLat

                    		
                  

                  

                    120
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    121
                    6x
                    
                      
      private$set_resolution()

                    		
                  

                  

                    122
                    
                    
                      
    },

                    		
                  

                  

                    123
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    124
                    
                    
                      
    #' @description Summary of the auxiliary longitude-latitude variable printed

                    		
                  

                  

                    125
                    
                    
                      
    #'   to the console.

                    		
                  

                  

                    126
                    
                    
                      
    print = function() {

                    		
                  

                  

                    127
                    !
                    
                      
      cat("<", self$friendlyClassName, ">\n", sep = "")

                    		
                  

                  

                    128
                    !
                    
                      
      cat("Longitude grid :", private$.varLong$name, "\n")

                    		
                  

                  

                    129
                    !
                    
                      
      cat("Latitude grid  :", private$.varLat$name, "\n")

                    		
                  

                  

                    130
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    131
                    !
                    
                      
      ext <- self$extent

                    		
                  

                  

                    132
                    !
                    
                      
      cat(sprintf("\nLongitude range: [%5.3f ... %5.3f] degrees_east\n", ext[1], ext[2]))

                    		
                  

                  

                    133
                    !
                    
                      
      cat(sprintf("Latitude range : [%5.3f ... %5.3f] degrees_north\n", ext[3], ext[4]))

                    		
                  

                  

                    134
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    135
                    !
                    
                      
      if (inherits(private$.aoi, "AOI")) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    136
                    !
                    
                      
        aoi <- private$.aoi

                    		
                  

                  

                    137
                    !
                    
                      
        cat(sprintf("\nAOI  longitude : [%5.3f ... %5.3f] degrees_east\n", aoi$lonMin, aoi$lonMax))

                    		
                  

                  

                    138
                    !
                    
                      
        cat(sprintf("      latitude : [%5.3f ... %5.3f] degrees_north\n", aoi$latMin, aoi$latMax))

                    		
                  

                  

                    139
                    !
                    
                      
        aoidim <- aoi$dim

                    		
                  

                  

                    140
                    !
                    
                      
        aoires <- aoi$resolution

                    		
                  

                  

                    141
                    !
                    
                      
        cat(sprintf("    resolution : [%5.3f degrees_east x %5.3f degrees_north]\n", aoires[1L], aoires[2L]))

                    		
                  

                  

                    142
                    !
                    
                      
        cat(sprintf("        extent : [%d rows x %d columns]", aoidim[1L], aoidim[2L]))

                    		
                  

                  

                    143
                    
                    
                      
      } else

                    		
                  

                  

                    144
                    !
                    
                      
        cat("\nAOI            : (not set)\n")

                    		
                  

                  

                    145
                    
                    
                      
    },

                    		
                  

                  

                    146
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    147
                    
                    
                      
    #' @description Some details of the auxiliary longitude-latitude grid.

                    		
                  

                  

                    148
                    
                    
                      
    #' @return A 2-row `data.frame` with some details of the grid components.

                    		
                  

                  

                    149
                    
                    
                      
    brief = function() {

                    		
                  

                  

                    150
                    1x
                    
                      
      lon <- private$.varLong

                    		
                  

                  

                    151
                    1x
                    
                      
      lat <- private$.varLat

                    		
                  

                  

                    152
                    1x
                    
                      
      out <- data.frame(axis = c("X", "Y"),

                    		
                  

                  

                    153
                    1x
                    
                      
                        name = c(lon$name, lat$name))

                    		
                  

                  

                    154
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    155
                    1x
                    
                      
      if (!identical(lon$longname, lon$name) || !identical(lat$longname, lat$name))

                    		
                  

                  

                    156
                    1x
                    
                      
        out[["long_name"]] <- c(lon$longname, lat$longname)

                    		
                  

                  

                    157
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    158
                    1x
                    
                      
      ext <- self$extent

                    		
                  

                  

                    159
                    1x
                    
                      
      out[["extent"]] <- c(sprintf("[%5.3f ... %5.3f]", ext[1], ext[2]),

                    		
                  

                  

                    160
                    1x
                    
                      
                           sprintf("[%5.3f ... %5.3f]", ext[3], ext[4]))

                    		
                  

                  

                    161
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    162
                    1x
                    
                      
      out[["unit"]] <- c("degrees_east", "degrees_north")

                    		
                  

                  

                    163
                    1x
                    
                      
      out

                    		
                  

                  

                    164
                    
                    
                      
    },

                    		
                  

                  

                    165
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    166
                    
                    
                      
    #' @description Return the indexes into the X (longitude) and Y (latitude)

                    		
                  

                  

                    167
                    
                    
                      
    #'   axes of the original data grid of the points closest to the supplied

                    		
                  

                  

                    168
                    
                    
                      
    #'   longitudes and latitudes, up to a maximum distance.

                    		
                  

                  

                    169
                    
                    
                      
    #' @param x,y Vectors of longitude and latitude values in decimal degrees,

                    		
                  

                  

                    170
                    
                    
                      
    #'   respectively.

                    		
                  

                  

                    171
                    
                    
                      
    #' @param maxDist Numeric value in decimal degrees of the maximum distance

                    		
                  

                  

                    172
                    
                    
                      
    #'   between the sampling point and the closest grid cell. If omitted

                    		
                  

                  

                    173
                    
                    
                      
    #'   (default), the distance is calculated from the nominal resolution of

                    		
                  

                  

                    174
                    
                    
                      
    #'   the grids.

                    		
                  

                  

                    175
                    
                    
                      
    #' @return A matrix with two columns `X` and `Y` and as many rows as

                    		
                  

                  

                    176
                    
                    
                      
    #'   arguments `x` and `y`. The `X` and `Y` columns give the index into the

                    		
                  

                  

                    177
                    
                    
                      
    #'   grid of the sampling points, or `c(NA, NA)` is no grid point is located

                    		
                  

                  

                    178
                    
                    
                      
    #'   within the `maxDist` distance from the sampling point.

                    		
                  

                  

                    179
                    
                    
                      
    sample_index = function(x, y, maxDist = NULL) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    180
                    2x
                    
                      
      if (is.null(x) || is.null(y) || length(x) != length(y))

                    		
                  

                  

                    181
                    !
                    
                      
        stop("Arguments `x` and `y` must be vectors of the same length", call. = FALSE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    182
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    183
                    2x
                    
                      
      if (is.null(maxDist))

                    		
                  

                  

                    184
                    2x
                    
                      
        maxDist <- max(private$.res)

                    		
                  

                  

                    185
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    186
                    2x
                    
                      
      varlon <- private$.varLong$read_data()

                    		
                  

                  

                    187
                    2x
                    
                      
      varlat <- private$.varLat$read_data()

                    		
                  

                  

                    188
                    2x
                    
                      
      out <- mapply(function(lon, lat, max2) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    189
                    2x
                    
                      
        dlon <- varlon - lon

                    		
                  

                  

                    190
                    2x
                    
                      
        dlat <- varlat - lat

                    		
                  

                  

                    191
                    2x
                    
                      
        dist2 <- dlon * dlon + dlat * dlat

                    		
                  

                  

                    192
                    2x
                    
                      
        min <- which.min(dist2)

                    		
                  

                  

                    193
                    2x
                    
                      
        if (dist2[min] <= max2) min else NA_integer_

                    		
                  

                  

                    194
                    2x
                    
                      
      }, x, y, MoreArgs = list(max2 = maxDist * maxDist))

                    		
                  

                  

                    195
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    196
                    2x
                    
                      
      out <- arrayInd(out, dim(varlon))

                    		
                  

                  

                    197
                    2x
                    
                      
      colnames(out) <- c("X", "Y")

                    		
                  

                  

                    198
                    2x
                    
                      
      out

                    		
                  

                  

                    199
                    
                    
                      
    },

                    		
                  

                  

                    200
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    201
                    
                    
                      
    #' @description Compute the indices for the AOI into the data grid.

                    		
                  

                  

                    202
                    
                    
                      
    #' @return An integer matrix with the dimensions of the AOI, where each

                    		
                  

                  

                    203
                    
                    
                      
    #' grid cell gives the linear index value into the longitude and latitude

                    		
                  

                  

                    204
                    
                    
                      
    #' grids.

                    		
                  

                  

                    205
                    
                    
                      
    grid_index = function() {

                    		
                  

                  

                    206
                    
                    
                      
      # Use the cached index, if available

                    		
                  

                  

                    207
                    !
                    
                      
      if (!is.null(private$.index)) return(private$.index)

                    		
                  

                  

                    208
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    209
                    
                    
                      
      # Otherwise calculate it

                    		
                  

                  

                    210
                    2x
                    
                      
      if (is.null(private$.aoi))

                    		
                  

                  

                    211
                    !
                    
                      
        private$setAOI(aoi())

                    		
                  

                  

                    212
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    213
                    
                    
                      
      # Orient AOI with the grid (for aoires and aoidim). AOI is always North

                    		
                  

                  

                    214
                    
                    
                      
      # up but the grid may be oriented differently, hence why indices into AOI

                    		
                  

                  

                    215
                    
                    
                      
      # properties aoires and aoidim are determined based on the orientation.

                    		
                  

                  

                    216
                    
                    
                      
      # Create vectors of AOI longitude and latitude coordinates.

                    		
                  

                  

                    217
                    2x
                    
                      
      lat <- private$.varLat$read_data()

                    		
                  

                  

                    218
                    2x
                    
                      
      lon <- private$.varLong$read_data()

                    		
                  

                  

                    219
                    2x
                    
                      
      aoiext <- private$.aoi$extent

                    		
                  

                  

                    220
                    2x
                    
                      
      aoidim <- private$.aoi$dim

                    		
                  

                  

                    221
                    2x
                    
                      
      aoires <- private$.aoi$resolution

                    		
                  

                  

                    222
                    2x
                    
                      
      if (private$.axis_order[1L] == "X") {

                    		
                  

                  

                    223
                    2x
                    
                      
        Xidx <- 1L; Yidx <- 2L

                    		
                  

                  

                    224
                    2x
                    
                      
        aoiY <- seq(from = aoiext[1L] + aoires[1L] * 0.5, by = aoires[1L], length.out = aoidim[2L])

                    		
                  

                  

                    225
                    2x
                    
                      
        aoiX <- seq(from = aoiext[3L] + aoires[2L] * 0.5, by = aoires[2L], length.out = aoidim[1L])

                    		
                  

                  

                    226
                    2x
                    
                      
        gridX <- lat

                    		
                  

                  

                    227
                    2x
                    
                      
        gridY <- lon

                    		
                  

                  

                    228
                    
                    
                      
      } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    229
                    !
                    
                      
        Xidx <- 2L; Yidx <- 1L

                    		
                  

                  

                    230
                    !
                    
                      
        aoiX <- seq(from = aoiext[1L] + aoires[1L] * 0.5, by = aoires[1L], length.out = aoidim[2L])

                    		
                  

                  

                    231
                    !
                    
                      
        aoiY <- seq(from = aoiext[3L] + aoires[2L] * 0.5, by = aoires[2L], length.out = aoidim[1L])

                    		
                  

                  

                    232
                    !
                    
                      
        gridX <- lon

                    		
                  

                  

                    233
                    !
                    
                      
        gridY <- lat

                    		
                  

                  

                    234
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    235
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    236
                    
                    
                      
      # Find pixels in the full grid that are within the AOI

                    		
                  

                  

                    237
                    2x
                    
                      
      grid <- (lon >= aoiext[1L]) & (lon < aoiext[2L]) &

                    		
                  

                  

                    238
                    2x
                    
                      
              (lat >= aoiext[3L]) & (lat < aoiext[4L])

                    		
                  

                  

                    239
                    2x
                    
                      
      if (!any(grid)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    240
                    !
                    
                      
        private$.index <- matrix(NA_integer_, aoidim[Yidx], aoidim[Xidx])

                    		
                  

                  

                    241
                    !
                    
                      
        dimnames(private$.index) <- list(aoiY, aoiX)

                    		
                  

                  

                    242
                    !
                    
                      
        return(private$.index)

                    		
                  

                  

                    243
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    244
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    245
                    2x
                    
                      
      grid_idx <- seq_len(prod(dim(lon)))[grid]

                    		
                  

                  

                    246
                    2x
                    
                      
      gridX <- gridX[grid]

                    		
                  

                  

                    247
                    2x
                    
                      
      gridY <- gridY[grid]

                    		
                  

                  

                    248
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    249
                    
                    
                      
      # Build the index for the AOI extent

                    		
                  

                  

                    250
                    2x
                    
                      
      out <- data.frame(aoiY)

                    		
                  

                  

                    251
                    2x
                    
                      
      for (x in 1L:aoidim[Xidx]) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    252
                    165x
                    
                      
        nearx <- abs(gridX - aoiX[x]) < (aoires[Xidx] * 2) # * 2 for buffer

                    111

    #' @description Read all the data from the file and turn the data into a

    #' @description Read some data from the file and turn the data into a

                    		
                  

                  

                    164

                    165

                    166
                    
                    
                      
    #'   This method returns a bare-bones matrix without any metadata or other

                    		
                  

                  

                    167
                    
                    
                      
    #'   identifying information. Use method `subset()` or the `[` operator

                    		
                  

                  

                    168
                    
                    
                      
    #'   rather than this method to obtain a more informative result.

                    		
                  

                  

                    169
                    
                    
                      
    #' @param start,count Start and count vectors that delimit the geographic

    read_chunk = function(start, count) {

    #' @description This method extracts a subset of values from the data of the

                    		
                  

                  

                    177
                    
                    
                      
    #'   variable, with the range along both axes expressed in decimal degrees.

                    		
                  

                  

                    178
                    
                    
                      
    #'

                    		
                  

                  

                    179
                    
                    
                      
    #' @details The range of values along both axes of latitude and longitude is

                    		
                  

                  

                    180
                    
                    
                      
    #'   expressed in decimal degrees. Any axes for which no information is

                    		
                  

                  

                    181
                    
                    
                      
    #'   provided in the `subset` argument are extracted in whole. Values can be

                    		
                  

                  

                    182
                    
                    
                      
    #'   specified in a variety of ways that should (resolve to) be a vector of

                    		
                  

                  

                    183
                    
                    
                      
    #'   real values. A range (e.g. `100:200`), a vector (`c(23, 46, 3, 45,

                    		
                  

                  

                    184
                    
                    
                      
    #'   17`), a sequence (`seq(from = 78, to = 100, by = 2`), all work. Note,

                    		
                  

                  

                    185
                    
                    
                      
    #'   however, that only a single range is generated from the vector so these

                    		
                  

                  

                    186
                    
                    
                      
    #'   examples resolve to `(100, 200)`, `(3, 46)`, and `(78, 100)`,

                    		
                  

                  

                    187
                    
                    
                      
    #'   respectively.

                    		
                  

                  

                    188
                    
                    
                      
    #'

                    		
                  

                  

                    189
                    
                    
                      
    #'   If the range of values for an axis in argument `subset` extend the

                    		
                  

                  

                    190
                    
                    
                      
    #'   valid range of the axis in `x`, the extracted slab will start at the

                    		
                  

                  

                    191
                    
                    
                      
    #'   beginning for smaller values and extend to the end for larger values.

                    		
                  

                  

                    192
                    
                    
                      
    #'   If the values envelope the valid range the entire axis will be

                    		
                  

                  

                    193
                    
                    
                      
    #'   extracted in the result. If the range of `subset` values for any axis

                    		
                  

                  

                    194
                    
                    
                      
    #'   are all either smaller or larger than the valid range of the axis in

                    		
                  

                  

                    195
                    
                    
                      
    #'   `x` then nothing is extracted and `NULL` is returned.

                    		
                  

                  

                    196
                    
                    
                      
    #'

                    		
                  

                  

                    197
                    
                    
                      
    #'   The extracted data has the same dimensional structure as the data in

                    		
                  

                  

                    198
                    
                    
                      
    #'   the variable, with degenerate dimensions dropped. The order of the axes

                    		
                  

                  

                    199
                    
                    
                      
    #'   in argument `subset` does not reorder the axes in the result; use the

                    		
                  

                  

                    200
                    
                    
                      
    #'   [CFVariable]$array() method for this.

                    		
                  

                  

                    201
                    
                    
                      
    #'

                    		
                  

                  

                    202
                    
                    
                      
    #' @param ... One or more arguments of the form `axis = range`. The "axis"

                    		
                  

                  

                    203
                    
                    
                      
    #'   part should be the name of axis `longitude` or `latitude` or its

                    		
                  

                  

                    204
                    
                    
                      
    #'   orientation `X` or `Y`. The "range" part is a vector of values

                    		
                  

                  

                    205
                    
                    
                      
    #'   representing coordinates along the axis where to extract data. Axis

                    		
                  

                  

                    206
                    
                    
                      
    #'   designators and names are case-sensitive and can be specified in any

                    		
                  

                  

                    207
                    
                    
                      
    #'   order. If values for the range of an axis fall outside of the extent of

                    		
                  

                  

                    208
                    
                    
                      
    #'   the axis, the range is clipped to the extent of the axis.

                    		
                  

                  

                    209
                    
                    
                      
    #' @param rightmost.closed Single logical value to indicate if the upper

                    		
                  

                  

                    210
                    
                    
                      
    #'   boundary of range in each axis should be included.

                    		
                  

                  

                    211
                    
                    
                      
    #'

                    		
                  

                  

                    212
                    
                    
                      
    #' @return A [CFVariable] instance, having an array with axes and attributes of

                    		
                  

                  

                    213
                    
                    
                      
    #'   the variable, or `NULL` if one or more of the elements in the `...`

                    		
                  

                  

                    214
                    
                    
                      
    #'   argument falls entirely outside of the range of the axis. Note that

                    		
                  

                  

                    215
                    
                    
                      
    #'   degenerate dimensions (having `length(.) == 1`) are dropped from the

                    		
                  

                  

                    216
                    
                    
                      
    #'   array but the corresponding axis is maintained in the result as a

                    		
                  

                  

                    217
                    
                    
                      
    #'   scalar axis.

                    		
                  

                  

                    218
                    
                    
                      
    subset = function(..., rightmost.closed = FALSE) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    219
                    
                    
                      
      # Organize the selectors

                    		
                  

                  

                    220
                    1x
                    
                      
      selectors <- list(...)

                    		
                  

                  

                    221
                    1x
                    
                      
      if (is.list(selectors[[1L]]))

                    		
                  

                  

                    222
                    !
                    
                      
        selectors <- selectors[[1L]]

                    		
                  

                  

                    223
                    1x
                    
                      
      sel_names <- names(selectors)

                    		
                  

                  

                    224
                    1x
                    
                      
      axis_names <- names(self$axes)

                    		
                  

                  

                    225
                    1x
                    
                      
      axis_order <- private$check_names(sel_names)

                    		
                  

                  

                    226
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    227
                    1x
                    
                      
      start <- c(1L, 1L)

                    		
                  

                  

                    228
                    1x
                    
                      
      count <- c(self$axes[[1L]]$length, self$axes[[2L]]$length)

                    		
                  

                  

                    229
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    230
                    1x
                    
                      
      out_axes_dim <- list()

                    		
                  

                  

                    231
                    1x
                    
                      
      out_axes_other <- list()

                    		
                  

                  

                    232
                    1x
                    
                      
      for (ax in seq_along(self$axes)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    233
                    3x
                    
                      
        axis <- self$axes[[ax]]

                    		
                  

                  

                    234
                    3x
                    
                      
        orient <- axis$orientation

                    		
                  

                  

                    235
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    236
                    3x
                    
                      
        rng <- NULL

                    		
                  

                  

                    237
                    3x
                    
                      
        if (is.null(rng)) rng <- selectors[[ axis_names[ax] ]]

                    		
                  

                  

                    238
                    1x
                    
                      
        if (is.null(rng)) rng <- selectors[[ orient ]]

                    		
                  

                  

                    239
                    3x
                    
                      
        if (is.null(rng)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    240
                    1x
                    
                      
          out_axis <- axis$copy()

                    		
                  

                  

                    241
                    
                    
                      
        } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    242
                    2x
                    
                      
          idx <- axis$slice(rng)

                    		
                  

                  

                    243
                    !
                    
                      
          if (is.null(idx)) return(NULL)

                    		
                  

                  

                    244
                    2x
                    
                      
          start[ax] <- idx[1L]

                    		
                  

                  

                    245
                    2x
                    
                      
          count[ax] <- idx[2L] - idx[1L] + 1L

                    		
                  

                  

                    246
                    2x
                    
                      
          out_axis <- axis$subset(rng = idx)

                    		
                  

                  

                    247
                    
                    
                      
        }

                    		
                  

                  

                    248
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    249
                    
                    
                      
        # Collect axes for result

                    		
                  

                  

                    250
                    3x
                    
                      
        if (out_axis$length == 1L)

                    		
                  

                  

                    251
                    1x
                    
                      
          out_axes_other <- append(out_axes_other, out_axis)

                    		
                  

                  

                    252
                    
                    
                      
        else

                    		
                  

                  

                    253
                    2x
                    
                      
          out_axes_dim <- append(out_axes_dim, out_axis)

                    		
                  

                  

                    254
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    255
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    256
                    
                    
                      
      # Read the data

                    		
                  

                  

                    257
                    1x
                    
                      
      d <- self$read_chunk(start, count)

                    		
                  

                  

                    258
                    1x
                    
                      
      d <- drop(d)

                    		
                  

                  

                    259
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    260
                    
                    
                      
      # Assemble the CFVariable instance

                    		
                  

                  

                    261
                    1x
                    
                      
      axes <- c(out_axes_dim, out_axes_other)

                    		
                  

                  

                    262
                    1x
                    
                      
      names(axes) <- sapply(axes, function(a) a$name)

                    		
                  

                  

                    263
                    1x
                    
                      
      v <- CFVariable$new(self$name, values = d, axes = axes, attributes = self$attributes)

                    		
                  

                  

                    264
                    1x
                    
                      
      v$crs <- self$crs

                    		
                  

                  

                    265
                    1x
                    
                      
      v

                    		
                  

                  

                    266
                    
                    
                      
    }
